1
00:00:19,269 --> 00:00:20,769
Where's the other Yong-jin?

2
00:00:20,770 --> 00:00:21,937
- Where did he go?
- Get back here.

3
00:00:21,938 --> 00:00:23,022
Hey, Lee Yong-jin.

4
00:00:23,023 --> 00:00:26,024
- Isn't this going overboard?
- Right?

5
00:00:26,025 --> 00:00:27,861
This is too far.

6
00:00:28,528 --> 00:00:31,905
But the thing is,
there must be a reason he came.

7
00:00:31,906 --> 00:00:33,032
Yes, of course.

8
00:00:33,033 --> 00:00:35,325
Is he an NIX member?

9
00:00:35,326 --> 00:00:37,786
His voice even sounded familiar.

10
00:00:37,787 --> 00:00:38,746
- Really?
- Yes.

11
00:00:38,747 --> 00:00:42,791
<i>Your security status is now
in the danger zone.</i>

12
00:00:42,792 --> 00:00:45,503
<i>Please wait here for a moment.</i>

13
00:01:10,862 --> 00:01:13,531
- Oh, this is the room with bricks.
- It was on the video.

14
00:01:17,118 --> 00:01:20,205
If we can't escape,
we'll die by explosion.

15
00:01:23,500 --> 00:01:25,502
So, how do we get out?

16
00:01:46,064 --> 00:01:50,068
AGENTS OF MYSTERY SEASON 2

17
00:01:54,739 --> 00:01:55,781
<i>They put us in prison.</i>

18
00:01:55,782 --> 00:01:59,160
<i>And bricks started falling
like we saw in the video.</i>

19
00:01:59,786 --> 00:02:01,995
<i>First of all, we started to panic.</i>

20
00:02:01,996 --> 00:02:03,789
Is there anything to solve?

21
00:02:03,790 --> 00:02:05,375
There's a blue one too.

22
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:09,879
<i>The bricks were falling
at a terrifying speed.</i>

23
00:02:10,880 --> 00:02:12,882
<i>I was afraid they would crush us.</i>

24
00:02:14,551 --> 00:02:16,094
- Why are they like that?
- What?

25
00:02:16,594 --> 00:02:17,929
They have different lengths.

26
00:02:18,555 --> 00:02:20,305
- The bulbs?
- Yes.

27
00:02:20,306 --> 00:02:22,767
- Stop falling.
- Will they light up if we twist them?

28
00:02:25,478 --> 00:02:26,688
It doesn't, does it?

29
00:02:27,856 --> 00:02:28,897
NO CHANGE

30
00:02:28,898 --> 00:02:30,483
If that's not it…

31
00:02:33,319 --> 00:02:35,487
Let's try using the key cards.

32
00:02:35,488 --> 00:02:37,197
Can you try holding them up close?

33
00:02:37,198 --> 00:02:39,032
TRYING WHATEVER THEY CAN

34
00:02:39,033 --> 00:02:39,868
Here?

35
00:02:40,994 --> 00:02:41,910
THE KEY CARD DOESN'T WORK

36
00:02:41,911 --> 00:02:43,121
- What can we do?
- Oh, my.

37
00:02:44,164 --> 00:02:45,164
What do we do?

38
00:02:45,165 --> 00:02:46,707
Are we supposed to insert this somewhere?

39
00:02:46,708 --> 00:02:48,168
What's happening?

40
00:02:49,294 --> 00:02:52,005
MEANWHILE, THE BRICKS ARE PILING UP

41
00:02:54,465 --> 00:02:55,508
This is crazy.

42
00:02:56,801 --> 00:02:57,759
Come this way.

43
00:02:57,760 --> 00:02:59,470
Move away. You'll get hit.

44
00:03:01,848 --> 00:03:04,017
- My feet keep sinking.
- Same.

45
00:03:05,602 --> 00:03:06,728
I keep sinking in.

46
00:03:07,353 --> 00:03:10,814
<i>There were no doors to open.</i>

47
00:03:10,815 --> 00:03:13,860
<i>So, I started searching the walls.</i>

48
00:03:15,653 --> 00:03:16,987
What's this?

49
00:03:16,988 --> 00:03:18,281
- What is it?
- This thing.

50
00:03:20,867 --> 00:03:23,660
<i>There was some kind of vent above.</i>

51
00:03:23,661 --> 00:03:25,204
A VENT?

52
00:03:25,788 --> 00:03:26,873
Today is really…

53
00:03:27,665 --> 00:03:29,166
- I couldn't see anything.
- Today is tough.

54
00:03:29,167 --> 00:03:30,584
It's really tough.

55
00:03:30,585 --> 00:03:32,128
- There's nothing here.
- Nothing?

56
00:03:32,712 --> 00:03:34,504
ANOTHER EMPTY DRAWER

57
00:03:34,505 --> 00:03:36,591
- There's nothing in there?
- It's empty.

58
00:03:37,550 --> 00:03:39,343
<i>You may leave now.</i>

59
00:03:39,344 --> 00:03:40,553
Can we?

60
00:03:41,137 --> 00:03:43,097
Which room do we go to?

61
00:03:46,267 --> 00:03:47,894
- Where do we go?
- I know, right?

62
00:03:48,478 --> 00:03:50,062
We don't have a key card.

63
00:03:50,063 --> 00:03:53,190
What if the other team has them?

64
00:03:53,191 --> 00:03:55,025
Their room was in that direction.

65
00:03:55,026 --> 00:03:57,153
- We should see them come out.
- Why won't they come out?

66
00:03:58,529 --> 00:03:59,822
We don't have a key card.

67
00:04:03,868 --> 00:04:06,955
ROOM 101 OPENS ON ITS OWN

68
00:04:10,708 --> 00:04:11,833
Room 101?

69
00:04:11,834 --> 00:04:14,671
ENTERING THROUGH THE OPEN DOOR FOR NOW

70
00:04:16,339 --> 00:04:18,216
- It's the Log-in Room.
- Yes.

71
00:04:19,467 --> 00:04:21,594
- It's moved locations.
- It has.

72
00:04:23,388 --> 00:04:26,723
NEW LOG-IN ROOM LOCATION

73
00:04:26,724 --> 00:04:30,310
LOG-IN ROOM LOCATION 4 HOURS AGO

74
00:04:30,311 --> 00:04:31,603
- Oh, my.
- That scared me.

75
00:04:31,604 --> 00:04:33,606
<i>Please close the door.</i>

76
00:04:34,399 --> 00:04:38,318
<i>The other three agents
who came to the Black Room</i>

77
00:04:38,319 --> 00:04:39,987
<i>have been recognized as hackers.</i>

78
00:04:39,988 --> 00:04:42,114
<i>-They have been locked away.</i>
- They got caught?

79
00:04:42,115 --> 00:04:45,325
<i>The Attacker neutralization protocol
will be activated soon.</i>

80
00:04:45,326 --> 00:04:48,245
<i>If you do not rescue the trapped agents,</i>

81
00:04:48,246 --> 00:04:50,665
<i>their lives will be in danger.</i>

82
00:04:51,291 --> 00:04:54,751
<i>The other agents were trapped
in the same room</i>

83
00:04:54,752 --> 00:04:56,628
<i>where the intruders had died.</i>

84
00:04:56,629 --> 00:04:59,089
<i>Will you save the trapped agents?</i>

85
00:04:59,090 --> 00:05:00,465
- Yes.
- Yes.

86
00:05:00,466 --> 00:05:01,758
Of course.

87
00:05:01,759 --> 00:05:03,218
Should we stack these bricks to climb up?

88
00:05:03,219 --> 00:05:05,262
- Let's try that.
- I think so.

89
00:05:05,263 --> 00:05:07,180
I'll stack these over here.

90
00:05:07,181 --> 00:05:09,642
BEGINS STACKING THE BLOCKS TO ONE SIDE

91
00:05:10,226 --> 00:05:12,311
I think we are meant to go up.

92
00:05:12,312 --> 00:05:13,312
- Really?
- Why?

93
00:05:13,313 --> 00:05:15,772
That's the only way out.

94
00:05:15,773 --> 00:05:18,859
ESCAPE THROUGH THE VENT?

95
00:05:18,860 --> 00:05:20,695
I like vents.

96
00:05:21,529 --> 00:05:23,864
FROM SEASON 1
KIM DO-HOON LIKES VENTS

97
00:05:23,865 --> 00:05:25,324
Once we found the vent,

98
00:05:25,325 --> 00:05:27,743
I was less scared of the bricks falling,

99
00:05:27,744 --> 00:05:30,038
and I wanted them to pile up quickly.

100
00:05:34,167 --> 00:05:35,876
Are you trying to go up?

101
00:05:35,877 --> 00:05:36,711
NODS

102
00:05:38,087 --> 00:05:39,504
- Be careful.
- Move them here.

103
00:05:39,505 --> 00:05:41,549
THEY'RE PILING THE BLOCKS FROM BELOW

104
00:05:46,721 --> 00:05:47,763
It's opening.

105
00:05:47,764 --> 00:05:48,805
- It opens.
- It does?

106
00:05:48,806 --> 00:05:49,973
- Really?
- Yes.

107
00:05:49,974 --> 00:05:52,142
- Be careful.
- But it only opens a little.

108
00:05:52,143 --> 00:05:54,479
DO-HOON CANNOT RESIST VENTS

109
00:05:56,105 --> 00:05:58,107
- It's blocked by something.
- What?

110
00:05:59,275 --> 00:06:01,110
- What did you say?
- It's blocked.

111
00:06:02,111 --> 00:06:04,405
- It does open, but it's blocked.
- It is?

112
00:06:04,989 --> 00:06:06,573
<i>There had to be something within reach.</i>

113
00:06:06,574 --> 00:06:09,410
<i>I tried to feel around for a key.</i>

114
00:06:09,994 --> 00:06:11,953
Wait, there's some kind of button.

115
00:06:11,954 --> 00:06:13,121
- There's a button?
- Yes.

116
00:06:13,122 --> 00:06:14,122
DIALS FOUND

117
00:06:14,123 --> 00:06:17,167
There's some kind of control button.

118
00:06:17,168 --> 00:06:18,251
IT TURNED ON

119
00:06:18,252 --> 00:06:19,711
- Hey, you did great.
- Look, the light's turned on.

120
00:06:19,712 --> 00:06:22,089
Good job. Keep going.

121
00:06:22,090 --> 00:06:22,924
There you go.

122
00:06:23,758 --> 00:06:24,801
I'm turning it.

123
00:06:25,343 --> 00:06:27,761
- Is it a button or a dial?
- It's a dial.

124
00:06:27,762 --> 00:06:29,429
Is there just one?

125
00:06:29,430 --> 00:06:31,681
- Yes. No, wait a minute.
- Oh, no.

126
00:06:31,682 --> 00:06:33,016
There are four dials.

127
00:06:33,017 --> 00:06:34,476
- There are four, right?
- Yes.

128
00:06:34,477 --> 00:06:35,686
- In that case…
- I'll turn them all on.

129
00:06:36,437 --> 00:06:38,355
TWISTING AND TURNING

130
00:06:38,356 --> 00:06:39,357
Why isn't it working?

131
00:06:40,566 --> 00:06:43,110
NO CHANGE IN THE BULBS

132
00:06:43,111 --> 00:06:47,406
- Maybe there's a way to turn them all on.
- I see.

133
00:06:48,199 --> 00:06:50,158
WHAT COULD IT BE?

134
00:06:50,159 --> 00:06:54,621
I thought I could turn the lights on
by using the dials correctly,

135
00:06:54,622 --> 00:06:58,208
but the lights turned on and off randomly.

136
00:06:58,209 --> 00:06:59,376
Can I try?

137
00:06:59,377 --> 00:07:00,795
Yeah, want to give it a shot?

138
00:07:01,546 --> 00:07:02,629
- Watch out.
- Okay.

139
00:07:02,630 --> 00:07:05,341
PLAYER SUBSTITUTION

140
00:07:07,718 --> 00:07:09,679
Do we need to turn them all on?

141
00:07:10,179 --> 00:07:11,931
Let's turn them all on if possible.

142
00:07:14,809 --> 00:07:17,811
HYE-RI IS NOT TURNING THE DIALS

143
00:07:17,812 --> 00:07:20,690
BUT THE LIGHT IS BLINKING

144
00:07:21,649 --> 00:07:24,277
I'm not turning the dials,
but the light's still blinking.

145
00:07:25,403 --> 00:07:28,739
THE LIGHT IS BLINKING ON ITS OWN

146
00:07:29,782 --> 00:07:32,118
Wait, could this be a signal?

147
00:07:33,703 --> 00:07:34,911
It's a signal.

148
00:07:34,912 --> 00:07:37,415
WHO'S SENDING THE SIGNAL?

149
00:07:38,833 --> 00:07:41,376
IT'S A SIGNAL FROM US

150
00:07:41,377 --> 00:07:43,545
15 MINUTES EARLIER

151
00:07:43,546 --> 00:07:46,089
<i>Will you save the trapped agents?</i>

152
00:07:46,090 --> 00:07:47,340
- Yes.
- Yes.

153
00:07:47,341 --> 00:07:48,258
Of course.

154
00:07:48,259 --> 00:07:50,552
<i>The key card will take you to a new room.</i>

155
00:07:50,553 --> 00:07:52,888
<i>You can help
your fellow agents from there.</i>

156
00:07:52,889 --> 00:07:54,932
This is crazy. Are we doing this again?

157
00:07:56,184 --> 00:07:57,767
What is this?

158
00:07:57,768 --> 00:08:00,062
QUICKLY MOVING TO ROOM 201

159
00:08:05,651 --> 00:08:06,693
Is it 5943?

160
00:08:06,694 --> 00:08:07,777
ENTERING ROOM 201

161
00:08:07,778 --> 00:08:09,030
It's a red room.

162
00:08:10,364 --> 00:08:11,364
GASP

163
00:08:11,365 --> 00:08:13,241
So, we can see them from here.

164
00:08:13,242 --> 00:08:14,743
Oh, no.

165
00:08:14,744 --> 00:08:16,161
It must be so hot in there.

166
00:08:16,162 --> 00:08:17,787
- I feel so bad for them.
- Right?

167
00:08:17,788 --> 00:08:18,915
What's this?

168
00:08:19,582 --> 00:08:20,790
There are four buttons.

169
00:08:20,791 --> 00:08:21,917
I know what this is.

170
00:08:21,918 --> 00:08:24,127
- This makes the light bulbs flash.
- I think so.

171
00:08:24,128 --> 00:08:26,004
I think we should try
pressing the buttons.

172
00:08:26,005 --> 00:08:29,758
Do you think the bulbs will be affected
if we press the buttons?

173
00:08:29,759 --> 00:08:31,134
Here we go.

174
00:08:31,135 --> 00:08:32,762
PRESSING THE BUTTONS

175
00:08:33,513 --> 00:08:35,890
- Hey, you did great.
- Look, the light's turned on.

176
00:08:37,225 --> 00:08:39,142
We're using the bulbs as a signal.

177
00:08:39,143 --> 00:08:40,685
Okay.

178
00:08:40,686 --> 00:08:42,604
We're supposed to send signals
using the bulbs

179
00:08:42,605 --> 00:08:45,190
- to move the dials into position.
- Yes, we have to match them.

180
00:08:45,191 --> 00:08:46,025
Okay.

181
00:08:46,526 --> 00:08:48,443
- It's a signal.
- It is.

182
00:08:48,444 --> 00:08:49,861
Is it Morse code?

183
00:08:49,862 --> 00:08:51,363
One, two, three,

184
00:08:51,364 --> 00:08:54,283
- four, five, six, seven, eight…
- Four, five, six, seven, eight…

185
00:08:54,909 --> 00:08:58,453
BUT THE BLINKING GETS FASTER

186
00:08:58,454 --> 00:09:00,998
- What does it mean?
- What are they telling us?

187
00:09:01,499 --> 00:09:03,124
If you're watching this,

188
00:09:03,125 --> 00:09:04,584
- send us the signal again.
- Yes.

189
00:09:04,585 --> 00:09:06,212
Go again from the start.

190
00:09:06,712 --> 00:09:08,171
We'll count it.

191
00:09:08,172 --> 00:09:09,506
Turn the lights off.

192
00:09:09,507 --> 00:09:10,674
- Start again.
- Reset.

193
00:09:10,675 --> 00:09:11,800
WE CAN'T HEAR YOU

194
00:09:11,801 --> 00:09:13,260
YOU KNOW THIS FEELING, RIGHT?

195
00:09:13,261 --> 00:09:15,345
I don't think they can hear us.

196
00:09:15,346 --> 00:09:16,514
- Really?
- Yes.

197
00:09:17,181 --> 00:09:20,308
- Let's start once they slow down.
- Okay.

198
00:09:20,309 --> 00:09:22,686
We were thinking of ways to signal them.

199
00:09:22,687 --> 00:09:26,523
We came up with the idea
of a metal detector.

200
00:09:26,524 --> 00:09:29,484
A BEEP THAT GETS FASTER AS YOU GET CLOSER

201
00:09:29,485 --> 00:09:32,737
We thought that was
the best way to guide them.

202
00:09:32,738 --> 00:09:34,197
The closer they got to the arrows,

203
00:09:34,198 --> 00:09:37,367
<i>the faster the lights would blink.</i>

204
00:09:37,368 --> 00:09:40,453
<i>Once the dial lands on the arrows,
we'd hold the button</i>

205
00:09:40,454 --> 00:09:41,997
and keep the light on.

206
00:09:41,998 --> 00:09:43,416
I'll take the second light bulb.

207
00:09:44,125 --> 00:09:45,834
Signal the second one only.

208
00:09:45,835 --> 00:09:47,211
That's it. Wait.

209
00:09:47,795 --> 00:09:50,463
TURN THE SECOND DIAL

210
00:09:50,464 --> 00:09:52,007
Do they want us to turn the second dial?

211
00:09:52,008 --> 00:09:53,300
- Try it.
- I think so.

212
00:09:53,301 --> 00:09:54,260
Do it slowly.

213
00:09:56,512 --> 00:09:58,138
<i>Signal the second one only.</i>

214
00:09:58,139 --> 00:09:59,432
That's it. Wait.

215
00:10:00,099 --> 00:10:01,933
- That's it!
- Okay.

216
00:10:01,934 --> 00:10:04,561
Would it be better
if Yong-jin did the first one?

217
00:10:04,562 --> 00:10:07,814
YONG-JIN IS IN CHARGE
OF THE FIRST LIGHT BULB

218
00:10:07,815 --> 00:10:09,858
TURN THE FIRST DIAL

219
00:10:09,859 --> 00:10:11,526
SHOULD I GO FOR DIAL 1? DIAL 2? DIAL 3?

220
00:10:11,527 --> 00:10:12,736
CONFUSED FUMBLING

221
00:10:12,737 --> 00:10:14,280
- That's it.
- That's the one.

222
00:10:14,947 --> 00:10:16,364
Yes, go on.

223
00:10:16,365 --> 00:10:17,282
BACK TO DIAL 2

224
00:10:17,283 --> 00:10:18,742
NOW DIAL 3

225
00:10:18,743 --> 00:10:20,493
Press it. Okay, that's good.

226
00:10:20,494 --> 00:10:22,329
WHAT NEXT?

227
00:10:22,330 --> 00:10:23,330
DIAL 3 AGAIN

228
00:10:23,331 --> 00:10:24,831
Come on!

229
00:10:24,832 --> 00:10:27,083
It wasn't easy to communicate.

230
00:10:27,084 --> 00:10:29,337
On top of that, Hye-ri…

231
00:10:29,920 --> 00:10:32,131
I think she's practicing to be a DJ.

232
00:10:33,841 --> 00:10:34,966
Do one at a time.

233
00:10:34,967 --> 00:10:35,884
HEY, ARE YOU LISTENING?

234
00:10:35,885 --> 00:10:37,427
Are you watching us?

235
00:10:37,428 --> 00:10:38,511
Are you listening?

236
00:10:38,512 --> 00:10:39,804
Do one at a time.

237
00:10:39,805 --> 00:10:41,348
Let's do one at a time.

238
00:10:41,349 --> 00:10:42,641
- Yong-jin.
- That's it.

239
00:10:42,642 --> 00:10:43,559
Your turn.

240
00:10:44,477 --> 00:10:45,894
Stay on that dial.

241
00:10:45,895 --> 00:10:47,771
- Just keep signaling that one.
- Okay.

242
00:10:47,772 --> 00:10:50,148
It's the first bulb,
so just keep turning the first dial.

243
00:10:50,149 --> 00:10:51,191
Keep turning.

244
00:10:51,192 --> 00:10:53,234
TURNING DIAL 1

245
00:10:53,235 --> 00:10:54,152
It worked.

246
00:10:54,153 --> 00:10:55,945
<i>Okay, that should do.</i>

247
00:10:55,946 --> 00:10:57,072
<i>Yes, let's move on.</i>

248
00:10:57,073 --> 00:10:58,865
Does that mean dials 1 and 2 are done?

249
00:10:58,866 --> 00:11:00,742
- Let's move to the third.
- Yes, Karina's turn.

250
00:11:00,743 --> 00:11:02,744
Okay, it's working.

251
00:11:02,745 --> 00:11:04,496
- That's okay. We can try again.
- Yes.

252
00:11:04,497 --> 00:11:06,539
Should we turn the third dial?

253
00:11:06,540 --> 00:11:08,876
Let's try the third dial.

254
00:11:09,377 --> 00:11:11,836
- You're getting close.
- A little more.

255
00:11:11,837 --> 00:11:13,588
- They must be pressing the buttons.
- Yes.

256
00:11:13,589 --> 00:11:14,506
Keep going.

257
00:11:14,507 --> 00:11:15,591
- A little more.
- Keep going.

258
00:11:17,802 --> 00:11:19,219
- Just a bit more.
- That's it.

259
00:11:19,220 --> 00:11:20,929
- Does that mean we did it?
- Ta-da.

260
00:11:20,930 --> 00:11:22,847
THEY CLEARED THE 3RD DIAL!

261
00:11:22,848 --> 00:11:23,890
<i>Keep turning.</i>

262
00:11:23,891 --> 00:11:26,018
THE FINAL FOURTH DIAL

263
00:11:26,602 --> 00:11:27,520
Keep going.

264
00:11:28,145 --> 00:11:29,438
<i>You have to turn it a bit more.</i>

265
00:11:29,939 --> 00:11:33,401
- That's it. Good.
- You're doing great.

266
00:11:33,984 --> 00:11:35,528
Stop right when it stops blinking.

267
00:11:36,112 --> 00:11:37,071
Turn it slowly.

268
00:11:37,571 --> 00:11:39,406
You can do this.

269
00:11:39,407 --> 00:11:40,783
<i>It's getting closer.</i>

270
00:11:41,409 --> 00:11:42,450
<i>That's it.</i>

271
00:11:42,451 --> 00:11:44,494
- Okay.
- Stop, send the stop signal.

272
00:11:44,495 --> 00:11:45,412
It's done, right?

273
00:11:45,413 --> 00:11:46,872
- It's done.
- We did it.

274
00:11:47,790 --> 00:11:49,040
We did it.

275
00:11:49,041 --> 00:11:50,083
- Okay.
- That was hard.

276
00:11:50,084 --> 00:11:51,000
MISSION COMPLETE

277
00:11:51,001 --> 00:11:52,044
Great job, everyone.

278
00:11:52,628 --> 00:11:53,879
- Good job.
- That was…

279
00:11:54,380 --> 00:11:55,673
- We did it.
- We did it.

280
00:11:56,966 --> 00:11:58,758
- It's done.
- Great job, Hye-ri.

281
00:11:58,759 --> 00:12:00,176
- Good job.
- You did great.

282
00:12:00,177 --> 00:12:04,222
I kept a really close eye on the signal,

283
00:12:04,223 --> 00:12:06,433
and I tried to stop moving the dial

284
00:12:06,434 --> 00:12:09,018
as soon as the bulb stopped blinking.

285
00:12:09,019 --> 00:12:10,855
That's when it finally worked.

286
00:12:11,981 --> 00:12:13,607
What's going on? The engine just started.

287
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:15,358
- What?
- What?

288
00:12:15,359 --> 00:12:16,944
- What?
- We're moving?

289
00:12:17,486 --> 00:12:18,903
- What?
- What?

290
00:12:18,904 --> 00:12:19,822
What's going on?

291
00:12:20,489 --> 00:12:21,739
- What's going on?
- What's happening?

292
00:12:21,740 --> 00:12:22,866
Are we going somewhere?

293
00:12:22,867 --> 00:12:24,284
THE ROOM STARTS TO MOVE

294
00:12:24,285 --> 00:12:25,702
WHAT IS HAPPENING?

295
00:12:25,703 --> 00:12:26,828
- What the…
- Where are we going?

296
00:12:26,829 --> 00:12:27,997
- My gosh!
- Hang on.

297
00:12:28,622 --> 00:12:30,416
- Why are they…
- What's going on?

298
00:12:32,334 --> 00:12:33,877
Shouldn't the door open?

299
00:12:33,878 --> 00:12:35,295
Right?

300
00:12:35,296 --> 00:12:36,463
What's going on?

301
00:12:36,464 --> 00:12:38,339
They won't vanish, will they?

302
00:12:38,340 --> 00:12:39,549
No way.

303
00:12:39,550 --> 00:12:40,801
Is this a vehicle?

304
00:12:41,677 --> 00:12:42,845
It wasn't earlier.

305
00:12:43,596 --> 00:12:44,637
We're moving?

306
00:12:44,638 --> 00:12:45,890
- What's going on?
- We're moving.

307
00:12:46,724 --> 00:12:48,808
<i>-How can this be a car? It can't be.
- What's going on?</i>

308
00:12:48,809 --> 00:12:50,019
<i>Wasn't this just a room?</i>

309
00:12:52,771 --> 00:12:53,688
What is going on?

310
00:12:53,689 --> 00:12:54,856
THE DOOR SUDDENLY OPENS

311
00:12:54,857 --> 00:12:56,233
- It's open.
- Let's go.

312
00:12:56,901 --> 00:12:58,318
Come this way.

313
00:12:58,319 --> 00:13:00,278
- What on earth?
- We're over here.

314
00:13:00,279 --> 00:13:01,196
- Is that you, Yong-jin?
- No way.

315
00:13:01,197 --> 00:13:02,113
- Come here.
- I'll help you push.

316
00:13:02,114 --> 00:13:03,448
- Karina!
- Yong-jin.

317
00:13:03,449 --> 00:13:05,116
Come down.

318
00:13:05,117 --> 00:13:06,493
What just happened?

319
00:13:06,494 --> 00:13:07,661
What is this?

320
00:13:08,829 --> 00:13:10,455
HYE-RI ESCAPES

321
00:13:10,456 --> 00:13:11,915
- Did you hear us?
- Yes.

322
00:13:11,916 --> 00:13:13,041
Can you go down, Gabee?

323
00:13:13,042 --> 00:13:13,876
Hang on.

324
00:13:14,835 --> 00:13:16,002
GABEE ESCAPES

325
00:13:16,003 --> 00:13:16,962
Take your time.

326
00:13:19,423 --> 00:13:21,090
LASTLY, DO-HOON ESCAPES

327
00:13:21,091 --> 00:13:23,092
- Be careful, Do-hoon.
- Watch your ankle.

328
00:13:23,093 --> 00:13:24,344
- Oh, I see.
- What is going on?

329
00:13:24,345 --> 00:13:25,303
Is this where you were?

330
00:13:25,304 --> 00:13:27,223
- Yes.
- Were you watching us from here?

331
00:13:27,723 --> 00:13:29,098
FINALLY REUNITED

332
00:13:29,099 --> 00:13:30,267
That was wild.

333
00:13:32,603 --> 00:13:36,106
<i>The Trackers are on high alert.</i>

334
00:13:37,316 --> 00:13:40,276
<i>Your security status
is in the danger zone.</i>

335
00:13:40,277 --> 00:13:43,531
<i>Moving to the next defense barrier
is practically impossible.</i>

336
00:13:44,031 --> 00:13:48,661
<i>For maximum security,
the gateway will be deactivated.</i>

337
00:13:49,245 --> 00:13:50,620
<i>From now on,</i>

338
00:13:50,621 --> 00:13:53,707
<i>you must move
as calmly and quietly as you can.</i>

339
00:13:55,042 --> 00:13:55,876
What's that?

340
00:13:58,295 --> 00:14:00,214
FLASHLIGHT?

341
00:14:03,259 --> 00:14:05,301
- It's a flashlight.
- What's the room number?

342
00:14:05,302 --> 00:14:07,679
I think we'll be moving in the dark.

343
00:14:07,680 --> 00:14:09,055
What is this?

344
00:14:09,056 --> 00:14:12,016
We received three of these earlier.

345
00:14:12,017 --> 00:14:13,393
30 MINUTES EARLIER
THE DRAWER OPENED

346
00:14:13,394 --> 00:14:14,978
What is this?

347
00:14:14,979 --> 00:14:19,899
<i>The items next to the key card
will help you avoid the Trackers.</i>

348
00:14:19,900 --> 00:14:21,234
It's a smoke grenade.

349
00:14:21,235 --> 00:14:24,112
- It's to throw off the Trackers.
- I see.

350
00:14:24,113 --> 00:14:26,030
- I couldn't see a thing even from here.
- Really?

351
00:14:26,031 --> 00:14:27,282
- That's how dark it was?
- Yes.

352
00:14:27,283 --> 00:14:28,867
- It was pitch black.
- That's so scary.

353
00:14:28,868 --> 00:14:30,159
- I'll open the door.
- I had no idea.

354
00:14:30,160 --> 00:14:31,536
- We could see everything--
- Be quiet.

355
00:14:31,537 --> 00:14:33,873
Even the sound of footsteps was scary.

356
00:14:35,749 --> 00:14:37,501
- The lights are off.
- Turn the flashlight on.

357
00:14:38,878 --> 00:14:40,879
PITCH BLACK DARKNESS

358
00:14:40,880 --> 00:14:43,923
<i>When we stepped out,
all the lights were off.</i>

359
00:14:43,924 --> 00:14:47,928
<i>It felt like something critical</i>

360
00:14:48,512 --> 00:14:49,429
was about to happen.

361
00:14:49,430 --> 00:14:50,889
- Let's be quiet.
- Yes.

362
00:14:50,890 --> 00:14:51,849
Stay calm.

363
00:14:52,808 --> 00:14:53,851
It's this door.

364
00:14:56,395 --> 00:14:58,272
A SERIES OF SENTENCES IN ENGLISH

365
00:14:59,273 --> 00:15:01,775
A KEY CARD WITH IRREGULAR BLANK SPACES

366
00:15:02,443 --> 00:15:03,444
What could it be?

367
00:15:03,944 --> 00:15:05,321
Is it something to do with numbers?

368
00:15:05,863 --> 00:15:06,946
There it is.

369
00:15:06,947 --> 00:15:07,865
Three.

370
00:15:10,910 --> 00:15:12,410
Do we match the card on number three?

371
00:15:12,411 --> 00:15:13,829
I don't see anything.

372
00:15:15,039 --> 00:15:17,790
Is this where we place the numbers?

373
00:15:17,791 --> 00:15:18,708
Is this it?

374
00:15:18,709 --> 00:15:22,421
WHAT IF THEY MATCH THE NUMBERS
TO THE BLANKS?

375
00:15:25,883 --> 00:15:27,468
Try entering 1984.

376
00:15:28,052 --> 00:15:29,219
That's a good one.

377
00:15:31,472 --> 00:15:32,723
- It worked.
- It's right.

378
00:15:40,356 --> 00:15:41,231
What's this now?

379
00:15:45,569 --> 00:15:48,697
<i>There were colorful objects on the ground.</i>

380
00:15:49,281 --> 00:15:50,657
Do we step on them?

381
00:15:50,658 --> 00:15:51,867
What could this be?

382
00:15:56,622 --> 00:15:57,830
What's that?

383
00:15:57,831 --> 00:15:58,998
A SUDDEN COUNTDOWN

384
00:15:58,999 --> 00:16:00,833
- It's a dance game.
- Do we get ready?

385
00:16:00,834 --> 00:16:02,460
- Is it like <i>Rhythm Star?</i>
- It's <i>Rhythm Star.</i>

386
00:16:02,461 --> 00:16:03,628
I think so.

387
00:16:03,629 --> 00:16:04,796
It is.

388
00:16:04,797 --> 00:16:06,547
- Everyone, pick a color.
- John, stand on red.

389
00:16:06,548 --> 00:16:08,257
- Pick a color.
- What is this?

390
00:16:08,258 --> 00:16:10,052
- We stomp like this. Press it.
- Suddenly?

391
00:16:15,391 --> 00:16:16,557
I'm sorry. My bad.

392
00:16:16,558 --> 00:16:18,142
- We step on that to start.
- I got it now.

393
00:16:18,143 --> 00:16:19,394
- This is the start button.
- Okay.

394
00:16:19,395 --> 00:16:20,979
- Let's just wing it.
- I stepped on it.

395
00:16:20,980 --> 00:16:23,982
Since we have
three singers and one dancer…

396
00:16:23,983 --> 00:16:25,317
We can do this.

397
00:16:25,943 --> 00:16:27,318
It's a piece of cake.

398
00:16:27,319 --> 00:16:29,654
It was a chance for me to shine.

399
00:16:29,655 --> 00:16:31,698
We have a dancer on the team.

400
00:16:31,699 --> 00:16:33,032
She's also a choreographer.

401
00:16:33,033 --> 00:16:34,450
What could go wrong?

402
00:16:34,451 --> 00:16:37,829
As long as Do-hoon kept up,
we could do it in no time.

403
00:16:37,830 --> 00:16:39,580
MISSION UNDERSTOOD
ROUND 2

404
00:16:39,581 --> 00:16:41,582
I'm really bad at this.

405
00:16:41,583 --> 00:16:45,254
ALL FIRED UP

406
00:16:54,722 --> 00:16:56,264
- Gabee.
- It's lagging.

407
00:16:56,265 --> 00:16:57,724
- Gabee.
- It's not working properly.

408
00:16:57,725 --> 00:16:59,058
BLAMING THE MACHINE

409
00:16:59,059 --> 00:17:00,226
- Try it.
- You see… Hang on.

410
00:17:00,227 --> 00:17:01,561
The beat goes like this.

411
00:17:01,562 --> 00:17:03,271
- This is the beat.
- Isn't it easier with one foot?

412
00:17:03,272 --> 00:17:04,814
BOOM BAP, BOOM BAP, BAP BAP BAP

413
00:17:04,815 --> 00:17:06,190
No, that's not the beat.

414
00:17:06,191 --> 00:17:07,067
Follow the music.

415
00:17:09,820 --> 00:17:10,654
Stomp.

416
00:17:11,196 --> 00:17:13,072
This is how you do it. Got it?

417
00:17:13,073 --> 00:17:14,949
Dance to the beat of the music.

418
00:17:14,950 --> 00:17:19,412
Games like <i>DDR</i> are about timing.

419
00:17:19,413 --> 00:17:22,540
You don't need to dance or look graceful.

420
00:17:22,541 --> 00:17:23,750
It's all about rhythm.

421
00:17:23,751 --> 00:17:25,502
You've got groove, John.

422
00:17:29,131 --> 00:17:30,174
Stomp three times.

423
00:17:33,385 --> 00:17:34,261
That's right.

424
00:17:35,846 --> 00:17:36,846
Something's wrong.

425
00:17:36,847 --> 00:17:37,681
- Gabee.
- It's the machine.

426
00:17:38,599 --> 00:17:41,685
It wasn't a rhythm I was used to.

427
00:17:42,686 --> 00:17:44,146
HESITATING

428
00:17:45,856 --> 00:17:48,232
- Stand here, Gabee.
- Okay.

429
00:17:48,233 --> 00:17:50,193
- We keep switching.
- What's happening?

430
00:17:50,194 --> 00:17:52,153
- It's a demotion.
- "Demotion"?

431
00:17:52,154 --> 00:17:53,154
John is rocking it.

432
00:17:53,155 --> 00:17:54,614
You're a dancer.

433
00:17:54,615 --> 00:17:57,826
JUST A RHYTHM GAME FOR JOHN

434
00:17:59,536 --> 00:18:01,037
You're off-beat.

435
00:18:01,038 --> 00:18:02,413
- Can I try?
- It has to be on the beat.

436
00:18:02,414 --> 00:18:03,956
- I'll give it a go.
- You try, Yong-jin.

437
00:18:03,957 --> 00:18:06,209
Gabee!

438
00:18:06,210 --> 00:18:09,546
RHYTHM LESSON FOR THE CHOREOGRAPHER

439
00:18:14,384 --> 00:18:16,761
- Come on, Hye-ri.
- You've got the hang of it, right?

440
00:18:16,762 --> 00:18:18,679
You understand, right?

441
00:18:18,680 --> 00:18:19,972
- Who's yellow?
- I'll do it.

442
00:18:19,973 --> 00:18:21,099
- Okay.
- This is quite hard.

443
00:18:21,100 --> 00:18:22,350
- Let's try.
- Let's try it.

444
00:18:22,351 --> 00:18:23,268
Let's do this.

445
00:18:27,314 --> 00:18:29,273
- I got it right this time.
- Me too.

446
00:18:29,274 --> 00:18:30,358
Blue's the culprit.

447
00:18:30,359 --> 00:18:32,652
- Gabee.
- I'll show you what happened.

448
00:18:32,653 --> 00:18:36,239
I thought she might be a double agent
who was messing up on purpose.

449
00:18:36,240 --> 00:18:37,490
I just…

450
00:18:37,491 --> 00:18:39,200
The thing is…

451
00:18:39,201 --> 00:18:40,577
I have no excuse.

452
00:18:45,582 --> 00:18:47,041
Show us, Gabee.

453
00:18:47,042 --> 00:18:49,043
TIME TO REALLY SHOW THEM

454
00:18:49,044 --> 00:18:50,838
It's your turn, Gabee.

455
00:18:52,422 --> 00:18:54,882
ROUND 10 ALREADY?

456
00:18:54,883 --> 00:18:58,428
TENSE

457
00:19:02,099 --> 00:19:03,808
FINALLY PASSED
BLUE PART AT BEGINNING

458
00:19:03,809 --> 00:19:04,934
Oh, no.

459
00:19:04,935 --> 00:19:05,852
CLENCHING TIGHTLY

460
00:19:05,853 --> 00:19:07,146
We're doing great.

461
00:19:13,527 --> 00:19:14,986
Okay, that was good.

462
00:19:14,987 --> 00:19:16,237
- Okay.
- That was good.

463
00:19:16,238 --> 00:19:17,738
What was that rhythm?

464
00:19:17,739 --> 00:19:19,073
- We can do it.
- There was a jump.

465
00:19:19,074 --> 00:19:20,951
- Yes, there was.
- We have to jump?

466
00:19:21,535 --> 00:19:22,827
<i>We need to use both feet?</i>

467
00:19:22,828 --> 00:19:24,537
A JUMP?

468
00:19:24,538 --> 00:19:26,831
In that case, this part's easy.

469
00:19:26,832 --> 00:19:27,790
Should I move here?

470
00:19:27,791 --> 00:19:29,167
- This part's easy.
- You're moving?

471
00:19:29,168 --> 00:19:30,835
- You take over yellow.
- Start?

472
00:19:30,836 --> 00:19:32,545
- Yes.
- Here we go.

473
00:19:32,546 --> 00:19:34,213
This is fun.

474
00:19:34,214 --> 00:19:35,382
It's a fun game.

475
00:19:36,550 --> 00:19:38,009
It's made for you.

476
00:19:38,010 --> 00:19:39,261
MADE JUST FOR HER
GOING ON ROUND 11

477
00:19:42,389 --> 00:19:43,764
Why?

478
00:19:43,765 --> 00:19:46,058
- Who was on red?
- Hye-ri.

479
00:19:46,059 --> 00:19:48,060
FOUND THE SECOND WEAK PLAYER

480
00:19:48,061 --> 00:19:49,729
CAN YOU GO OVER THERE?

481
00:19:49,730 --> 00:19:51,606
Are you going to keep switching, Hye-ri?

482
00:19:51,607 --> 00:19:53,107
You were great during your Girl's Day era.

483
00:19:53,108 --> 00:19:54,358
What's with you today?

484
00:19:54,359 --> 00:19:55,819
- I've seen you dance.
- You can do this.

485
00:19:56,486 --> 00:19:58,070
- You're a great dancer!
- Hye-ri.

486
00:19:58,071 --> 00:19:59,989
- I saw you pull this off.
- Forget Girl's Day.

487
00:19:59,990 --> 00:20:03,409
As soon as I saw the game,
I realized I was in trouble.

488
00:20:03,410 --> 00:20:06,204
I was praying the whole time.

489
00:20:06,205 --> 00:20:09,040
HANDS CLASPED TOGETHER

490
00:20:09,041 --> 00:20:10,750
FAILED

491
00:20:10,751 --> 00:20:13,169
SOMEONE LOOKS SUSPICIOUSLY HAPPY

492
00:20:13,170 --> 00:20:14,170
Excuse me, Hye-ri.

493
00:20:14,171 --> 00:20:15,422
How did you end up here?

494
00:20:16,215 --> 00:20:17,673
What are you doing there, Hye-ri?

495
00:20:17,674 --> 00:20:18,841
Why am I here?

496
00:20:18,842 --> 00:20:20,927
- Hye-ri, when did you get there?
- How did you get there?

497
00:20:20,928 --> 00:20:22,304
HYE-RI KEEPS SWITCHING TO THE EASY PARTS

498
00:20:22,888 --> 00:20:25,014
- Was that me? That was me.
- What happened?

499
00:20:25,015 --> 00:20:26,307
It was yellow and blue.

500
00:20:26,308 --> 00:20:27,225
That's me.

501
00:20:27,226 --> 00:20:30,228
Wait, are you playing with your hands
in your pockets, Do-hoon?

502
00:20:30,229 --> 00:20:31,146
No, I…

503
00:20:31,897 --> 00:20:33,314
- The thing is--
- Are you crazy?

504
00:20:33,315 --> 00:20:34,607
Let's not lose our temper.

505
00:20:34,608 --> 00:20:35,566
Let's stay calm.

506
00:20:35,567 --> 00:20:38,319
- Everybody, hold hands.
- Did he just…

507
00:20:38,320 --> 00:20:40,363
- He's trying to look cool.
- You two make up.

508
00:20:40,364 --> 00:20:41,739
- He's showing off.
- Make up.

509
00:20:41,740 --> 00:20:43,115
- Make up, already.
- Hear me out.

510
00:20:43,116 --> 00:20:45,661
I did it on purpose
because my arms were throwing me off beat.

511
00:20:46,245 --> 00:20:47,745
- This is the last part.
- Okay.

512
00:20:47,746 --> 00:20:49,455
PRIVATE LESSON IN SESSION

513
00:20:49,456 --> 00:20:51,249
Stomp three times after two beats.

514
00:20:51,250 --> 00:20:52,291
- Got it?
- Okay.

515
