843
00:33:12,907 --> 00:33:14,074
- I knew it.
- Walls are eliminated.

844
00:33:14,075 --> 00:33:15,075
- No more walls.
- Okay.

845
00:33:15,076 --> 00:33:16,493
- Okay.
- Great.

846
00:33:16,494 --> 00:33:17,744
- Should we go again?
- Let's go.

847
00:33:17,745 --> 00:33:18,705
Let's do it.

848
00:33:21,457 --> 00:33:23,334
It's okay to mess up!

849
00:33:23,876 --> 00:33:25,336
Just don't lose heart.

850
00:33:26,379 --> 00:33:27,421
- Let's do a cheer.
- Let's go.

851
00:33:27,422 --> 00:33:29,548
- This is the last time.
- Yes, the last.

852
00:33:29,549 --> 00:33:31,758
- This is really the last time.
- Hands down.

853
00:33:31,759 --> 00:33:32,718
One, two, three.

854
00:33:32,719 --> 00:33:33,635
- Let's go!
- Let's go!

855
00:33:33,636 --> 00:33:34,553
For the last time!

856
00:33:34,554 --> 00:33:36,763
CHANTING

857
00:33:36,764 --> 00:33:37,640
COPYING GABEE

858
00:33:38,641 --> 00:33:40,518
TIME TO POWER UP

859
00:33:42,145 --> 00:33:43,896
It's just a part of my life now.

860
00:33:44,772 --> 00:33:46,815
- It's now a part of me.
- Bring it, you rhythm prick.

861
00:33:46,816 --> 00:33:48,693
- You're so positive.
- "Rhythm prick."

862
00:33:49,360 --> 00:33:51,612
You're just a rhythm prick.

863
00:33:52,405 --> 00:33:55,950
STARTING STRONG

864
00:34:12,717 --> 00:34:14,427
HEY

865
00:34:29,108 --> 00:34:31,193
TRIPLETS

866
00:34:31,194 --> 00:34:32,945
PERFECTLY MASTERED

867
00:34:37,867 --> 00:34:39,326
COME AT US, YOU RHYTHM PRICK!

868
00:34:39,327 --> 00:34:41,079
SINGING ALONG

869
00:34:42,288 --> 00:34:43,581
DANCING TO THE BEAT

870
00:34:47,794 --> 00:34:51,421
AFTER COUNTLESS FAILS

871
00:34:51,422 --> 00:34:55,051
NOW PERFECTLY IN SYNC

872
00:34:58,888 --> 00:35:00,681
SECOND BATCH OF TRIPLETS

873
00:35:03,059 --> 00:35:04,310
- Hold on.
- Let's do this.

874
00:35:05,853 --> 00:35:06,938
Wait!

875
00:35:08,106 --> 00:35:11,484
SUCCESS AT LAST

876
00:35:15,530 --> 00:35:16,948
We've been through a lot.

877
00:35:17,949 --> 00:35:21,118
- Great job.
- Unbelievable.

878
00:35:21,119 --> 00:35:22,160
It was the best feeling.

879
00:35:22,161 --> 00:35:23,411
I've never felt better.

880
00:35:23,412 --> 00:35:26,123
Can you tell us later
how many rounds it took?

881
00:35:26,124 --> 00:35:27,666
Didn't we do it at least 50 times?

882
00:35:27,667 --> 00:35:28,583
71 ROUNDS

883
00:35:28,584 --> 00:35:31,878
I think we were in there for hours.

884
00:35:31,879 --> 00:35:33,672
Were we in there for two hours?

885
00:35:33,673 --> 00:35:35,882
A GRUELING TWO-HOUR STRUGGLE

886
00:35:35,883 --> 00:35:38,552
It was so hard. I don't think I can walk.

887
00:35:38,553 --> 00:35:40,804
I don't have any energy left to go home.

888
00:35:40,805 --> 00:35:42,681
- Jeez!
- Great work.

889
00:35:42,682 --> 00:35:44,266
We couldn't have done it with the wall up.

890
00:35:44,267 --> 00:35:46,310
- Right?
- Yes, it was a good call.

891
00:35:47,270 --> 00:35:48,937
- I'm so tired.
- I'm so thirsty.

892
00:35:48,938 --> 00:35:50,898
I can taste blood in my mouth.

893
00:35:51,524 --> 00:35:52,358
Oh, gosh.

894
00:35:58,489 --> 00:35:59,782
What is that?

895
00:36:11,794 --> 00:36:13,211
- What was that?
- Was it a silkworm?

896
00:36:13,212 --> 00:36:15,214
It looked like some kind of spider.

897
00:36:15,840 --> 00:36:17,550
Didn't it look like an eyeball?

898
00:36:18,634 --> 00:36:20,051
<i>It looked like an eyeball.</i>

899
00:36:20,052 --> 00:36:22,512
It was covered in cobwebs.

900
00:36:22,513 --> 00:36:25,308
And it was twitching like this.

901
00:36:26,017 --> 00:36:30,145
It looked like some kind of spider den.

902
00:36:30,146 --> 00:36:34,024
Clips were of strange objects
flashed by really quickly.

903
00:36:34,025 --> 00:36:37,320
I thought they might be
supernatural phenomena.

904
00:36:37,904 --> 00:36:40,323
- Is the gauge down to red?
- Yes.

905
00:36:41,240 --> 00:36:42,574
We're in the danger zone.

906
00:36:42,575 --> 00:36:43,867
THE GAUGE IS AT DANGER LEVEL

907
00:36:43,868 --> 00:36:44,744
That's not…

908
00:36:45,536 --> 00:36:47,288
That's not our energy level, is it?

909
00:36:48,789 --> 00:36:50,123
It's not our energy level, is it?

910
00:36:50,124 --> 00:36:51,250
It matches.

911
00:36:52,043 --> 00:36:54,085
- We have to…
- We have to be quiet.

912
00:36:54,086 --> 00:36:55,128
We have to be really quiet.

913
00:36:55,129 --> 00:36:58,256
- We need to be ready to use these now.
- Okay.

914
00:36:58,257 --> 00:36:59,382
Let's go.

915
00:36:59,383 --> 00:37:00,676
- Which room's next?
- Room 208.

916
00:37:11,771 --> 00:37:18,402
THE AGENTS QUIETLY
MAKE THEIR WAY TO ROOM 208

917
00:37:20,154 --> 00:37:21,197
Let's solve the puzzle.

918
00:37:25,076 --> 00:37:28,245
GEOMETRIC DESIGNS
PLACED ALL OVER THE PUZZLE

919
00:37:28,246 --> 00:37:32,375
WHAT'S THE HIDDEN RULE?

920
00:37:37,421 --> 00:37:41,174
I feel like there's a way
to make it fit perfectly.

921
00:37:41,175 --> 00:37:45,263
THE AGENTS ARE CLUELESS

922
00:37:46,138 --> 00:37:47,139
What could it be?

923
00:37:52,228 --> 00:37:54,522
Instead of placing it directly on here,

924
00:37:55,690 --> 00:37:58,317
