BANG

974
00:39:59,522 --> 00:40:01,564
A NEVER-ENDING RHYTHM TRAP

975
00:40:01,565 --> 00:40:03,401
ARE WE OKAY?

976
00:40:08,447 --> 00:40:09,823
Can we go on it?

977
00:40:09,824 --> 00:40:11,283
We can't stand on it?

978
00:40:12,159 --> 00:40:13,827
Do you want to try?

979
00:40:13,828 --> 00:40:15,454
- Yes.
- Be careful.

980
00:40:15,955 --> 00:40:17,831
- Should we all try?
- Should we?

981
00:40:17,832 --> 00:40:19,999
- Should we try standing on it?
- Yes.

982
00:40:20,000 --> 00:40:21,668
- Let's stand on it.
- Do we use our weight?

983
00:40:21,669 --> 00:40:22,503
EVERYONE CLIMBS UP

984
00:40:23,754 --> 00:40:25,255
This is right.

985
00:40:25,256 --> 00:40:26,256
- It's starting.
- What is it?

986
00:40:26,257 --> 00:40:29,301
- Please.
- Do we follow our colors?

987
00:40:30,219 --> 00:40:32,137
- Go on, Yong-jin.
- It's a memory game.

988
00:40:32,138 --> 00:40:33,889
- You need to memorize it.
- It's a memory game?

989
00:40:35,057 --> 00:40:36,183
We need to remember it?

990
00:40:40,771 --> 00:40:42,314
Each person has to follow their path.

991
00:40:44,733 --> 00:40:45,692
THE ORANGE ROUTE STARTS RIGHT AWAY

992
00:40:45,693 --> 00:40:46,694
Okay.

993
00:40:47,319 --> 00:40:48,904
One, two, three, four…

994
00:40:51,198 --> 00:40:52,867
- Okay.
- This is better.

995
00:40:57,496 --> 00:40:59,165
- Yours is so easy.
- It's easy for me.

996
00:41:01,041 --> 00:41:02,168
Oh, my. What's this?

997
00:41:04,628 --> 00:41:05,463
That's so hard.

998
00:41:06,172 --> 00:41:08,465
Why are there so many?
Stop freaking spreading.

999
00:41:08,466 --> 00:41:09,382
- What?
- I'm sorry.

1000
00:41:09,383 --> 00:41:10,383
HER IDOL PERSONA LEFT IN SHOCK

1001
00:41:10,384 --> 00:41:11,718
- What's going on?
- This is too much.

1002
00:41:11,719 --> 00:41:12,635
Why are there so many?

1003
00:41:12,636 --> 00:41:15,680
- There's a pattern, Karina.
- Really?

1004
00:41:15,681 --> 00:41:17,432
- There's a pattern.
- There is.

1005
00:41:17,433 --> 00:41:18,350
How do we…

1006
00:41:24,648 --> 00:41:26,650
You need to remember the shapes.

1007
00:41:27,234 --> 00:41:28,234
This one's a heart.

1008
00:41:28,235 --> 00:41:29,320
It's a heart.

1009
00:41:31,113 --> 00:41:32,615
- I'll take a step back to check.
- A heart.

1010
00:41:33,365 --> 00:41:34,450
It was a heart.

1011
00:41:36,577 --> 00:41:37,911
I guess mine's a flower.

1012
00:41:37,912 --> 00:41:39,746
There's definitely a pattern.

1013
00:41:39,747 --> 00:41:41,040
Yours must be a flower.

1014
00:41:41,665 --> 00:41:42,957
- Maybe not.
- What is that?

1015
00:41:42,958 --> 00:41:44,083
I'm dizzy.

1016
00:41:44,084 --> 00:41:45,044
What is it?

1017
00:41:46,212 --> 00:41:47,170
What is this?

1018
00:41:47,171 --> 00:41:48,880
LOST

1019
00:41:48,881 --> 00:41:50,381
What was that?

1020
00:41:50,382 --> 00:41:51,634
This is really hard.

1021
00:41:53,302 --> 00:41:59,974
The creators tortured us physically,
and now, it's mental torture.

1022
00:41:59,975 --> 00:42:02,436
- It's red first.
- Yong-jin, it's your turn.

1023
00:42:02,978 --> 00:42:04,313
Let's give it a go.

1024
00:42:04,813 --> 00:42:05,730
YONG-JIN STEPS UP TO GO FIRST

1025
00:42:05,731 --> 00:42:07,190
The next one was right here.

1026
00:42:07,191 --> 00:42:08,359
Can you remember it?

1027
00:42:09,360 --> 00:42:10,485
Yes.

1028
00:42:10,486 --> 00:42:11,904
I think there were three in a row.

1029
00:42:13,322 --> 00:42:14,573
- Go forward.
- One step forward.

1030
00:42:15,741 --> 00:42:16,867
Go forward again.

1031
00:42:17,826 --> 00:42:18,869
Left?

1032
00:42:22,331 --> 00:42:24,290
This is too hard.

1033
00:42:24,291 --> 00:42:25,959
We need to memorize them all.

1034
00:42:25,960 --> 00:42:27,086
- We do.
- It's a group task.

1035
00:42:27,795 --> 00:42:29,003
RESET ROUTE

1036
00:42:29,004 --> 00:42:30,713
- Should we go up again?
- Let's do it.

1037
00:42:30,714 --> 00:42:34,634
- I think we have to do it together.
- Let's all focus.

1038
00:42:34,635 --> 00:42:35,885
Try to remember each other's.

1039
00:42:35,886 --> 00:42:37,137
- Let's all go up.
- Okay.

1040
00:42:37,805 --> 00:42:38,972
Here we go.

1041
00:42:38,973 --> 00:42:41,182
This is so hard.

1042
00:42:41,183 --> 00:42:43,226
FOCUS

1043
00:42:43,227 --> 00:42:45,270
MEMORIZE THEM ALL
SECOND ROUTE REVEALED

1044
00:42:45,271 --> 00:42:47,063
EVERYONE MEMORIZES YONG-JIN'S RED ROUTE

1045
00:42:47,064 --> 00:42:49,524
It goes down and then pivots.

1046
00:42:49,525 --> 00:42:51,235
EVERYONE USES THEIR OWN METHOD

1047
00:42:51,902 --> 00:42:54,946
That's a seven,
and at the end of the seven…

1048
00:42:54,947 --> 00:42:57,240
NEXT IS JOHN'S ORANGE ROUTE

1049
00:42:57,241 --> 00:42:59,784
TRACING THE ROUTE WITH HIS FEET

1050
00:42:59,785 --> 00:43:01,077
You're a dance machine, John.

1051
00:43:01,078 --> 00:43:03,037
You solve everything through dance.

1052
00:43:03,038 --> 00:43:04,582
It's worth a try.

1053
00:43:05,374 --> 00:43:07,834
Yellow was way easier than the rest.

1054
00:43:07,835 --> 00:43:10,921
So, I thought I should focus
on helping the others.

1055
00:43:12,590 --> 00:43:14,591
MEANWHILE

1056
00:43:14,592 --> 00:43:15,675
It's confusing, isn't it?

1057
00:43:15,676 --> 00:43:16,676
KARINA'S LONG GREEN ROUTE

1058
00:43:16,677 --> 00:43:18,845
Mine was the hardest.

1059
00:43:18,846 --> 00:43:22,181
Karina's was the trickiest.

1060
00:43:22,182 --> 00:43:27,145
It covered most of the stage,
and it moved at random.

1061
00:43:27,146 --> 00:43:29,897
A PATTERNLESS PATTERN

1062
00:43:29,898 --> 00:43:31,941
We need to help her out.

1063
00:43:31,942 --> 00:43:33,610
I was on blue.

1064
00:43:33,611 --> 00:43:35,904
It formed a heart shape.

1065
00:43:36,989 --> 00:43:38,824
<i>I think mine was relatively easy.</i>

1066
00:43:39,450 --> 00:43:41,285
FINALLY HYE-RI'S PURPLE ROUTE

1067
00:43:41,869 --> 00:43:43,661
QUIETLY SCANNING

1068
00:43:43,662 --> 00:43:44,746
After the first few steps,

1069
00:43:44,747 --> 00:43:47,791
I thought of going around Gabee,

1070
00:43:48,834 --> 00:43:50,585
then around Karina.

1071
00:43:50,586 --> 00:43:53,630
After that, I had to make a heart.

1072
00:43:53,631 --> 00:43:56,424
But instead of completing the heart,

1073
00:43:56,425 --> 00:43:57,383
I had to pivot.

1074
00:43:57,384 --> 00:44:01,554
That's the story I came up with
to memorize it.

1075
00:44:01,555 --> 00:44:03,181
It's going to take forever

1076
00:44:03,182 --> 00:44:04,599
- to get to my turn.
- Right?

1077
00:44:04,600 --> 00:44:06,309
Let's start.

1078
00:44:06,310 --> 00:44:10,104
SECOND ATTEMPT

1079
00:44:10,105 --> 00:44:12,231
- Go forward.
- Take two more steps.

1080
00:44:12,232 --> 00:44:13,316
I go this way.

1081
00:44:13,317 --> 00:44:14,735
- And then…
- Go forward.

1082
00:44:15,361 --> 00:44:16,694
It's this way, right?

1083
00:44:16,695 --> 00:44:18,614
- Take one more step.
- Three squares.

1084
00:44:19,198 --> 00:44:20,198
Now, take a diagonal step.

1085
00:44:20,199 --> 00:44:21,282
- Yes.
- You have to pivot.

1086
00:44:21,283 --> 00:44:22,492
Form number seven here.

1087
00:44:22,493 --> 00:44:23,826
- One more, right?
- Step sideways.

1088
00:44:23,827 --> 00:44:26,954
- Think of seven and take one more step.
- Seven.

1089
00:44:26,955 --> 00:44:28,165
ONE MORE STEP FORWARD

1090
00:44:29,416 --> 00:44:30,584
- Was it wrong?
- I guess so.

1091
00:44:31,460 --> 00:44:33,878
I even considered spitting on my squares

1092
00:44:33,879 --> 00:44:34,962
if that was allowed.

1093
00:44:34,963 --> 00:44:36,673
Forget everything else.

1094
00:44:36,674 --> 00:44:37,590
Let's pick one--

1095
00:44:37,591 --> 00:44:38,758
- My brain's not working.
- It's fine.

1096
00:44:38,759 --> 00:44:40,176
Let's get the first one perfect.

1097
00:44:40,177 --> 00:44:42,428
- Let's take it step by step.
- Yes.

1098
00:44:42,429 --> 00:44:44,264
ROUTES REVEALED FOR THE THIRD TIME

1099
00:44:48,644 --> 00:44:50,436
- Three steps.
- After the third step,

1100
00:44:50,437 --> 00:44:51,479
it's the number seven.

1101
00:44:51,480 --> 00:44:53,482
After the number seven,
you take four steps.

1102
00:44:54,108 --> 00:44:55,818
- Then, an L-shape.
- Okay, got it.

1103
00:44:56,443 --> 00:44:57,735
Let's not think about the rest.

1104
00:44:57,736 --> 00:44:59,404
Don't look at them.

1105
00:44:59,405 --> 00:45:03,699
SKIP THE OTHER ROUTES FOR NOW

1106
00:45:03,700 --> 00:45:05,118
- From here…
- Let's do this.

1107
00:45:05,119 --> 00:45:06,411
THIRD ATTEMPT

1108
00:45:06,412 --> 00:45:07,328
Go slowly.

1109
00:45:07,329 --> 00:45:08,579
- Take three steps.
- Three steps.

1110
00:45:08,580 --> 00:45:10,081
- Step forward.
- Take two steps forward.

1111
00:45:10,082 --> 00:45:11,416
- Take one more step.
- Here.

1112
00:45:11,417 --> 00:45:14,043
Step sideways. Take three steps forward.

1113
00:45:14,044 --> 00:45:16,254
- Go three squares, then step diagonally.
- Diagonal.

1114
00:45:16,255 --> 00:45:17,713
Take a step forward.

1115
00:45:17,714 --> 00:45:19,006
- It's this one, right?
- Yes.

1116
00:45:19,007 --> 00:45:20,508
- Take one more step.
- Yes, two squares.

1117
00:45:20,509 --> 00:45:22,051
- Then, go down.
- It's four steps down.

1118
00:45:22,052 --> 00:45:25,179
- One, two, three.
- One, two, three.

1119
00:45:25,180 --> 00:45:26,305
Two…

1120
00:45:26,306 --> 00:45:28,307
- Now, go diagonally.
- Here, right?

1121
00:45:28,308 --> 00:45:29,225
It was diagonal.

1122
00:45:29,226 --> 00:45:31,102
- It was an L shape.
- That's right, Yong-jin.

1123
00:45:31,103 --> 00:45:32,603
Take a step forward.

1124
00:45:32,604 --> 00:45:33,521
- It's here, right?
- Yes.

1125
00:45:33,522 --> 00:45:34,606
Take one step left.

1126
00:45:35,899 --> 00:45:36,816
Yes, take two steps.

1127
00:45:36,817 --> 00:45:38,401
- Good.
- Now, take one step diagonally.

1128
00:45:38,402 --> 00:45:39,402
- Here?
- Yes.

1129
00:45:39,403 --> 00:45:40,445
Wait, is that wrong?

1130
00:45:40,446 --> 00:45:41,737
- Is it this way?
- No, it's right.

1131
00:45:41,738 --> 00:45:42,697
- Yes.
- It's like this.

1132
00:45:42,698 --> 00:45:44,782
- Okay.
- One more step.

1133
00:45:44,783 --> 00:45:45,825
Isn't it this one?

1134
00:45:45,826 --> 00:45:48,578
- No, go straight.
- Okay, you're right.

1135
00:45:48,579 --> 00:45:49,955
RED COMPLETE
ON THE THIRD ATTEMPT

1136
00:45:51,415 --> 00:45:55,084
My fellow agents
did the memorizing for me.

1137
00:45:55,085 --> 00:45:57,044
<i>John, Karina, and Hye-ri did it.</i>

1138
00:45:57,045 --> 00:45:58,213
John, you're next.

1139
00:45:58,714 --> 00:46:01,591
You had to kind of sway from side to side.

1140
00:46:01,592 --> 00:46:03,051
- I need to move, don't I?
- Yes.

1141
00:46:04,094 --> 00:46:06,137
SWAYING

1142
00:46:06,138 --> 00:46:07,306
STARTING TO SWAY

1143
00:46:07,973 --> 00:46:10,017
- I think it went left.
- It did.

1144
00:46:11,268 --> 00:46:13,436
- Go, John.
- Good.

1145
00:46:13,437 --> 00:46:15,271
- You memorized it through dance.
- You're doing great.

1146
00:46:15,272 --> 00:46:16,689
- It was this one next.
- That's right.

1147
00:46:16,690 --> 00:46:18,191
- I step here.
- This one's next.

1148
00:46:18,192 --> 00:46:20,193
- I step diagonally here.
- Yes.

1149
00:46:20,194 --> 00:46:22,028
STRUTTING

1150
00:46:22,029 --> 00:46:25,072
- He's impressive.
- He learned through dance.

1151
00:46:25,073 --> 00:46:26,241
That's it.

1152
00:46:28,952 --> 00:46:31,621
You should be called Dancing Park.

1153
00:46:31,622 --> 00:46:32,955
I memorized it like a dance.

1154
00:46:32,956 --> 00:46:34,333
Has he always been this way?

1155
00:46:35,083 --> 00:46:37,293
I think doing YouTube has changed him.

1156
00:46:37,294 --> 00:46:38,211
Have you memorized it?

1157
00:46:38,212 --> 00:46:39,921
Take your time.

1158
00:46:39,922 --> 00:46:41,547
One more, and that's it.

1159
00:46:41,548 --> 00:46:43,007
SUCCEEDS IN 3 SECONDS

1160
00:46:43,008 --> 00:46:43,925
Your turn, Karina.

1161
00:46:43,926 --> 00:46:44,884
How do I do this?

1162
00:46:44,885 --> 00:46:47,011
- It's okay.
- You can do it.

1163
00:46:47,012 --> 00:46:48,596
Go slowly.

1164
00:46:48,597 --> 00:46:49,514
THE FIRST FEW ARE EASY

1165
00:46:49,515 --> 00:46:50,431
Yes, go up.

1166
00:46:50,432 --> 00:46:51,891
This way, and then…

1167
00:46:51,892 --> 00:46:53,518
- No, go right diagonally.
- Was it this way?

1168
00:46:53,519 --> 00:46:54,561
Yeah, that way.

1169
00:46:55,187 --> 00:46:57,146
Go forward diagonally.

1170
00:46:57,147 --> 00:46:58,397
IT'S YONG-JIN'S TURN TO HELP

1171
00:46:58,398 --> 00:46:59,649
You need to come down here.

1172
00:46:59,650 --> 00:47:00,775
Yes, that's it.

1173
00:47:00,776 --> 00:47:02,109
I don't think it went this far.

1174
00:47:02,110 --> 00:47:03,237
Was it three steps that way?

1175
00:47:04,112 --> 00:47:05,072
Go up.

1176
00:47:06,573 --> 00:47:08,616
I think it went this way.

1177
00:47:08,617 --> 00:47:09,825
- I see.
- That's it.

1178
00:47:09,826 --> 00:47:11,202
Now, come down here.

1179
00:47:11,203 --> 00:47:12,037
Oh, dear.

1180
00:47:13,205 --> 00:47:14,330
I think it went this way.

1181
00:47:14,331 --> 00:47:15,456
That's right.

1182
00:47:15,457 --> 00:47:16,374
It came down to here.

1183
00:47:16,375 --> 00:47:18,000
We're doing great. Let's help each other.

1184
00:47:18,001 --> 00:47:19,418
- Gabee's is easy.
- We can do it.

1185
00:47:19,419 --> 00:47:21,587
We just need to remember
Karina's and Hye-ri's.

1186
00:47:21,588 --> 00:47:23,589
Think of all the dancing we did.

1187
00:47:23,590 --> 00:47:25,007
- This is nothing.
- You're right.

1188
00:47:25,008 --> 00:47:26,551
- Go on up.
- Okay.

1189
00:47:26,552 --> 00:47:30,179
I think we need to focus
on mastering Karina's route.

1190
00:47:30,180 --> 00:47:31,514
Good idea.

1191
00:47:31,515 --> 00:47:32,431
ROUTE REVEALED FOR THE 4TH TIME

1192
00:47:32,432 --> 00:47:33,558
- I won't look.
- Yes.

1193
00:47:33,559 --> 00:47:35,269
Don't look. It will get in your head.

1194
00:47:35,852 --> 00:47:37,938
DO NOT LOOK

1195
00:47:38,647 --> 00:47:39,940
You can do this, Karina.

1196
00:47:42,192 --> 00:47:44,443
Three steps, then another three…

1197
00:47:44,444 --> 00:47:47,738
It was a constant zigzag pattern.

1198
00:47:47,739 --> 00:47:48,699
Step there…

1199
00:47:49,199 --> 00:47:52,952
I started with the tiles at the borders.

1200
00:47:52,953 --> 00:47:54,453
It was three steps forward.

1201
00:47:54,454 --> 00:47:55,788
Then I went, "yikes."

1202
00:47:55,789 --> 00:47:57,331
Three steps later, it was "yikes" again.

1203
00:47:57,332 --> 00:47:59,875
"Yikes" here and there.

1204
00:47:59,876 --> 00:48:01,044
That's how I memorized it.

1205
00:48:01,712 --> 00:48:04,297
I pictured myself tripping over.

1206
00:48:04,298 --> 00:48:05,548
"Yikes" here, and then…

1207
00:48:05,549 --> 00:48:06,757
You can do it.

1208
00:48:06,758 --> 00:48:07,968
GREEN ROUTE'S DEMONSTRATION IS OVER

1209
00:48:10,929 --> 00:48:12,389
I can do this.

1210
00:48:14,474 --> 00:48:15,600
4TH ATTEMPT

1211
00:48:15,601 --> 00:48:16,517
Good start.

1212
00:48:16,518 --> 00:48:17,643
A man who memorizes by rhythm.

1213
00:48:17,644 --> 00:48:19,478
It's the only way I can remember.

1214
00:48:19,479 --> 00:48:20,897
YONG-JIN, JOHN, DO-HOON
SUCCEED ONE AFTER ANOTHER

1215
00:48:21,648 --> 00:48:22,773
Here I go!

1216
00:48:22,774 --> 00:48:23,983
- You can do it.
- You've got this.

1217
00:48:23,984 --> 00:48:24,985
Let's do this.

1218
00:48:27,613 --> 00:48:29,447
Take three steps.

1219
00:48:29,448 --> 00:48:30,740
Yes.

1220
00:48:30,741 --> 00:48:33,075
- Go up one.
- Take one step and pivot.

1221
00:48:33,076 --> 00:48:34,410
Take three steps.

1222
00:48:34,411 --> 00:48:35,329
- Take a second step.
- Go up.

1223
00:48:36,079 --> 00:48:37,331
- Take a step down.
- Up to here.

1224
00:48:38,540 --> 00:48:39,457
This way…

1225
00:48:39,458 --> 00:48:40,750
- You need to get here.
- One more…

1226
00:48:40,751 --> 00:48:41,959
This way, and then…

1227
00:48:41,960 --> 00:48:42,960
- Turn again.
- Yikes.

1228
00:48:42,961 --> 00:48:44,170
That's it.

1229
00:48:44,171 --> 00:48:45,421
- Take two steps.
- Take your time.

1230
00:48:45,422 --> 00:48:46,797
- Turn again.
- Yikes.

1231
00:48:46,798 --> 00:48:48,466
One…

1232
00:48:48,467 --> 00:48:51,344
- From here, go that way.
- I think it was here.

1233
00:48:51,345 --> 00:48:53,137
- Yes, you need to come to here.
- That's right.

1234
00:48:53,138 --> 00:48:54,221
Come this way.

1235
00:48:54,222 --> 00:48:55,598
- Yikes.
- Yes, come all the way.

1236
00:48:55,599 --> 00:48:56,891
- That's not it!
- Isn't it this?

1237
00:48:56,892 --> 00:48:58,100
- Where do I go?
- Go that way.

1238
00:48:58,101 --> 00:48:59,353
That's it.

1239
00:48:59,936 --> 00:49:01,312
- I'll turn here.
- Yes.

1240
00:49:01,313 --> 00:49:02,855
- Yes, come this way.
- Here, right?

1241
00:49:02,856 --> 00:49:04,524
- Yes, it's this way.
- That's it.

1242
00:49:05,192 --> 00:49:06,275
I'll go this way.

1243
00:49:06,276 --> 00:49:07,319
- This is the next one.
- Wait.

1244
00:49:08,236 --> 00:49:09,904
- I think it was here.
- It was this then that.

1245
00:49:09,905 --> 00:49:11,822
- Wait, that's not it.
- From here, you need to get here.

1246
00:49:11,823 --> 00:49:12,740
No, this was blank.

1247
00:49:12,741 --> 00:49:13,658
There was one blank…

1248
00:49:13,659 --> 00:49:15,368
- Wait.
- Oh, there were two.

1249
00:49:15,369 --> 00:49:17,578
- Yes, it was this way.
- It went like this.

1250
00:49:17,579 --> 00:49:19,413
- I go this way.
- It's that one.

1251
00:49:19,414 --> 00:49:21,248
- Step here, then turn.
- Come this way.

1252
00:49:21,249 --> 00:49:22,291
Yes, you need to get there.

1253
00:49:22,292 --> 00:49:23,460
- Then…
- It's these three.

1254
00:49:24,753 --> 00:49:25,921
MAXIMUM DIFFICULTY
GREEN ROUTE SUCCESSFUL

1255
00:49:26,963 --> 00:49:27,922
Great job.

1256
00:49:27,923 --> 00:49:29,591
You did amazing.

1257
00:49:30,300 --> 00:49:32,218
Of course, everybody helped.

1258
00:49:32,219 --> 00:49:36,138
But I think I did a good job
by staying focused.

1259
00:49:36,139 --> 00:49:37,306
Wait a minute, Gabee.

1260
00:49:37,307 --> 00:49:38,725
- It's the heart shape.
- Step one.

1261
00:49:39,393 --> 00:49:40,768
- Go diagonally.
- Diagonal.

1262
00:49:40,769 --> 00:49:41,895
- Go up.
- Take one step…

1263
00:49:42,437 --> 00:49:43,896
- I take three steps.
- Go down.

1264
00:49:43,897 --> 00:49:46,148
- Take one step out.
- Take a step this way.

1265
00:49:46,149 --> 00:49:48,859
One, two, three…

1266
00:49:48,860 --> 00:49:50,945
It's another three steps.

1267
00:49:50,946 --> 00:49:51,946
- Diagonally.
- Two diagonal steps.

1268
00:49:51,947 --> 00:49:53,447
- Take two steps.
- Two steps.

1269
00:49:53,448 --> 00:49:54,740
It forms a V-shape here.

1270
00:49:54,741 --> 00:49:58,411
- That's it.
- One, two, three.

1271
00:49:58,412 --> 00:50:00,663
Now, step diagonally one more time.

1272
00:50:00,664 --> 00:50:02,457
Go straight after that.

1273
00:50:03,709 --> 00:50:05,209
BLUE SUCCEEDS ON THE FIRST ATTEMPT

1274
00:50:05,210 --> 00:50:06,752
- We all remember it, right?
- Yes.

1275
00:50:06,753 --> 00:50:07,795
FINALLY HYE-RI'S TURN ON PURPLE

1276
00:50:07,796 --> 00:50:09,840
I think she had most of it memorized.

1277
00:50:14,261 --> 00:50:16,763
FEARLESSLY GOING SOLO

1278
00:50:18,223 --> 00:50:22,518
To be honest, even while trying
to memorize the others,

1279
00:50:22,519 --> 00:50:25,021
I memorized mine too.

1280
00:50:25,939 --> 00:50:28,607
It was a heart shape.

1281
00:50:28,608 --> 00:50:29,942
Take one more step forward.

1282
00:50:29,943 --> 00:50:30,777
That's it.

1283
00:50:31,862 --> 00:50:34,739
CHARGING FORWARD

1284
00:50:34,740 --> 00:50:37,032
Take two more steps diagonally.

1285
00:50:37,033 --> 00:50:38,577
- Take two diagonal steps.
- That's right.

1286
00:50:39,202 --> 00:50:40,203
Come this way.

1287
00:50:41,288 --> 00:50:42,621
- Step here.
- That's it.

1288
00:50:42,622 --> 00:50:44,290
- That's right.
- This one's next.

1289
00:50:44,291 --> 00:50:45,207
Step here next.

1290
00:50:45,208 --> 00:50:46,209
That's it.

1291
00:50:46,918 --> 00:50:48,127
- Go back.
- Yes.

1292
00:50:48,128 --> 00:50:50,045
- It was three steps.
- That's right.

1293
00:50:50,046 --> 00:50:51,589
- Take three steps, then…
- One, two, three.

1294
00:50:51,590 --> 00:50:52,798
- That's it.
- Okay.

1295
00:50:52,799 --> 00:50:54,258
- Step once more. Okay!
- That's the end.

1296
00:50:54,259 --> 00:50:55,718
Okay!

1297
00:50:55,719 --> 00:50:58,555
MISSION SUCCESSFUL

1298
00:50:59,306 --> 00:51:03,018
- Nice!
- This is real teamwork.

1299
00:51:04,561 --> 00:51:06,020
- We did it faster than I thought.
- Yes.

1300
00:51:06,021 --> 00:51:08,564
I could never remember Karina's.

1301
00:51:08,565 --> 00:51:09,732
Let's go. Which room?

1302
00:51:09,733 --> 00:51:11,233
- I'm so tired.
- It's Room 109.

1303
00:51:11,234 --> 00:51:12,611
Room 109.

1304
00:51:13,904 --> 00:51:15,781
Be quiet.

1305
00:51:18,784 --> 00:51:20,035
It's right across from here.

1306
00:51:21,578 --> 00:51:27,000
QUIETLY MOVING TO ROOM 109

1307
00:51:28,084 --> 00:51:30,461
WELCOME

1308
00:51:30,462 --> 00:51:33,756
AN ASSORTMENT OF ICONS

1309
00:51:33,757 --> 00:51:36,176
MORE ICONS ON THE KEY CARD

1310
00:51:38,345 --> 00:51:40,930
THIS GOES HERE

1311
00:51:40,931 --> 00:51:45,017
FIRST TRYING TO MATCH THE IDENTICAL ICONS

1312
00:51:45,018 --> 00:51:46,769
That's not it. The flower.

1313
00:51:46,770 --> 00:51:48,104
The flower is the center.

1314
00:51:49,773 --> 00:51:51,315
- Make it overlap here.
- Okay.

1315
00:51:51,316 --> 00:51:52,359
MAKE THEM BOTH OVERLAP

1316
00:51:52,943 --> 00:51:53,984
- It's six.
- It's six.

1317
00:51:53,985 --> 00:51:55,694
We need to keep rotating it like this.

1318
00:51:55,695 --> 00:51:56,655
- Do it four times.
- Six.

1319
00:51:57,489 --> 00:51:58,405
One is the number six.

1320
00:51:58,406 --> 00:51:59,323
ROTATE THE KEY CARD 4 TIMES

1321
00:51:59,324 --> 00:52:00,950
It starts at 12 o'clock.

1322
00:52:00,951 --> 00:52:02,786
- There's a counterclockwise sign.
- Put it on here.

1323
00:52:03,370 --> 00:52:06,164
IS TURNING IT COUNTERCLOCKWISE THE ANSWER?

1324
00:52:06,998 --> 00:52:08,500
- The first number is nine.
- Okay.

1325
00:52:09,167 --> 00:52:11,043
- Nine and two…
- Two.

1326
00:52:11,044 --> 00:52:12,838
- It's 9256.
- It's 9256?

1327
00:52:15,549 --> 00:52:16,800
- That's wrong.
- Really?

1328
00:52:17,384 --> 00:52:19,678
- We need to find the starting point.
- It is…

1329
00:52:21,346 --> 00:52:23,974
BANG

1330
00:52:25,851 --> 00:52:26,685
Get back.

1331
00:52:30,272 --> 00:52:31,272
WHAT CAN THEY USE?

1332
00:52:31,273 --> 00:52:33,275
SMOKE GRENADES

1333
00:52:33,984 --> 00:52:36,193
- Release them! Hurry!
- Hurry!

1334
00:52:36,194 --> 00:52:38,612
THE TRACKERS CHARGE FORWARD FIERCELY

1335
00:52:38,613 --> 00:52:41,658
RUN TO SURVIVE

1336
00:52:55,630 --> 00:52:57,172
<i>Once we threw the smoke grenades,</i>

1337
00:52:57,173 --> 00:53:00,218
<i>the Trackers instantly stopped moving.</i>

1338
00:53:01,011 --> 00:53:06,015
They were like the agents in <i>The Matrix.</i>

1339
00:53:06,016 --> 00:53:07,725
I started to think
it was a computer program.

1340
00:53:07,726 --> 00:53:09,184
We used the grenades,
so we need to hurry.

1341
00:53:09,185 --> 00:53:10,603
- We have to hurry!
- We need to solve it.

1342
00:53:10,604 --> 00:53:11,896
Throw another one!

1343
00:53:11,897 --> 00:53:13,105
No, don't do that.

1344
00:53:13,106 --> 00:53:14,315
It was six, nine, and what else?

1345
00:53:14,316 --> 00:53:16,692
THE TRACKERS CAN MOVE AT ANY TIME

1346
00:53:16,693 --> 00:53:18,235
We have to try 2569.

1347
00:53:18,236 --> 00:53:20,029
There's an order.

1348
00:53:20,030 --> 00:53:21,906
THE ORDER DEPENDS ON THE STARTING NUMBER

1349
00:53:21,907 --> 00:53:22,824
Hurry.

1350
00:53:24,618 --> 00:53:25,660
Isn't that it?

1351
00:53:27,454 --> 00:53:29,413
- If we think of this as a heart…
- Heart?

1352
00:53:29,414 --> 00:53:31,749
That explains the clubs.

1353
00:53:31,750 --> 00:53:33,334
<i>- Yes.
- I didn't notice that.</i>

1354
00:53:33,335 --> 00:53:34,294
THE TEAR ICON WAS A HALF-HEART

1355
00:53:35,045 --> 00:53:37,046
THE DIRECTION ALSO GOES CLOCKWISE

1356
00:53:37,047 --> 00:53:38,255
- So, it's nine.
- Go down.

1357
00:53:38,256 --> 00:53:39,341
- It's six.
- Six.

1358
00:53:39,966 --> 00:53:41,091
- It's five.
- Five.

1359
00:53:41,092 --> 00:53:42,468
- Two.
- Okay.

1360
00:53:42,469 --> 00:53:44,220
- It's 9652.
- It's 9652.

1361
00:53:44,930 --> 00:53:46,263
- Try 9652 quickly.
- Okay.

1362
00:53:46,264 --> 00:53:47,514
Why is it wrong?

1363
00:53:47,515 --> 00:53:49,266
Try 6529.

1364
00:53:49,267 --> 00:53:50,393
Let's try that.

1365
00:53:50,977 --> 00:53:51,936
Is that not it?

1366
00:53:51,937 --> 00:53:54,480
- Try 5296.
- Try 5296.

1367
00:53:54,481 --> 00:53:55,648
WRONG

1368
00:53:55,649 --> 00:53:56,982
It has to be 2965.

1369
00:53:56,983 --> 00:53:58,484
- Yes, try 2965.
- I'll try it.

1370
00:53:58,485 --> 00:54:00,819
Let's try 2965.

1371
00:54:00,820 --> 00:54:02,030
Okay, let's go in.

1372
00:54:02,614 --> 00:54:04,406
- Go in.
- Run.

1373
00:54:04,407 --> 00:54:05,449
RUSHING INTO ROOM 109

1374
00:54:05,450 --> 00:54:07,201
Hurry, come on.

1375
00:54:07,202 --> 00:54:09,620
SIGH

1376
00:54:09,621 --> 00:54:11,413
10 YEARS TAKEN OFF OUR LIVES

1377
00:54:11,414 --> 00:54:14,249
They're really chasing after us now.

1378
00:54:14,250 --> 00:54:16,001
- Right?
- They came so close.

1379
00:54:16,002 --> 00:54:18,129
<i>-We have to be really careful now.
- It's scary.</i>

1380
00:54:22,050 --> 00:54:23,217
- What's this?
- Is it a castle?

1381
00:54:23,218 --> 00:54:25,928
What's this? We need to enter the answer.

1382
00:54:25,929 --> 00:54:28,889
ANSWER BOX

1383
00:54:28,890 --> 00:54:31,393
A KEYBOARD ON THE SIDE

1384
00:54:32,185 --> 00:54:35,187
AND A MYSTERIOUS OBJECT AT THE CENTER

1385
00:54:35,188 --> 00:54:40,860
There was a spotlight,
and some kind of art piece under it.

1386
00:54:45,073 --> 00:54:46,573
Do we use shadows for this?

1387
00:54:46,574 --> 00:54:47,783
There's a spotlight here.

1388
00:54:47,784 --> 00:54:50,494
Turn it around, Do-hoon.

1389
00:54:50,495 --> 00:54:51,412
- Does it move?
- Can we?

1390
00:54:51,413 --> 00:54:52,746
Yes, it moves.

1391
00:54:52,747 --> 00:54:55,290
I think we can turn it
and use the shadows in some way.

1392
00:54:55,291 --> 00:54:56,208
Like this.

1393
00:54:56,209 --> 00:54:57,626
USING THE SHADOW CAST ON THE FLOOR?

1394
00:54:57,627 --> 00:54:59,546
Right? Look at the shadows.

1395
00:55:01,047 --> 00:55:02,006
The shadows…

1396
00:55:02,007 --> 00:55:03,341
GLANCING OVER

1397
00:55:03,883 --> 00:55:06,010
Couldn't we use this for shadows?

1398
00:55:06,011 --> 00:55:11,974
It might be a hidden message
visible only from a certain angle.

1399
00:55:11,975 --> 00:55:13,267
You might be right.

1400
00:55:13,268 --> 00:55:15,352
A MESSAGE ONLY VISIBLE
FROM A CERTAIN ANGLE?

1401
00:55:15,353 --> 00:55:17,563
This is a bit suspicious.

1402
00:55:17,564 --> 00:55:19,482
This kind of looks like English.

1403
00:55:20,066 --> 00:55:21,692
- Do you see that at the bottom?
- Yes, wait.

1404
00:55:21,693 --> 00:55:23,402
- It looks like a letter.
- You're right.

1405
00:55:23,403 --> 00:55:24,862
Let's look from the other side.

1406
00:55:24,863 --> 00:55:26,030
Take a look from over there.

1407
00:55:26,031 --> 00:55:26,865
OBSERVING FROM BOTH SIDES

1408
00:55:28,825 --> 00:55:31,201
If you look here, that's a flipped E.

1409
00:55:31,202 --> 00:55:35,165
AN E FLIPPED THE WRONG WAY

1410
00:55:35,874 --> 00:55:38,125
I think it has to do with English.

1411
00:55:38,126 --> 00:55:39,419
- Stand over there.
- Okay.

1412
00:55:40,003 --> 00:55:42,212
I'M GOING

1413
00:55:42,213 --> 00:55:43,130
FLASHLIGHT ON

1414
00:55:43,131 --> 00:55:44,173
- Come closer.
- There it is.

1415
00:55:44,174 --> 00:55:46,508
- You can see a V.
- Is it "love"?

1416
00:55:46,509 --> 00:55:48,469
- It's showing on your body.
- It is LOVE.

1417
00:55:48,470 --> 00:55:50,262
- It's "love."
- That's it.

1418
00:55:50,263 --> 00:55:51,890
Yes, LOVE. Look at that.

1419
00:55:52,682 --> 00:55:56,351
TYPING WITH LOVE

1420
00:55:56,352 --> 00:55:57,519
Hit enter.

1421
00:55:57,520 --> 00:55:59,189
It's right, isn't it? We got it.

1422
00:55:59,814 --> 00:56:02,024
- We did it, right? Okay.
- We did it.

1423
00:56:02,025 --> 00:56:03,359
Oh, my heart.

1424
00:56:04,110 --> 00:56:06,904
Is this the last room?

1425
00:56:06,905 --> 00:56:10,116
- I think the next room's the last one.
- Yes, this is the tenth room.

1426
00:56:11,242 --> 00:56:12,827
Was there a zero?

1427
00:56:14,704 --> 00:56:16,789
- The room at the end.
- You're right.

1428
00:56:16,790 --> 00:56:20,834
Rooms on each side
started with 100 or 200.

1429
00:56:20,835 --> 00:56:22,087
<i>But suddenly, there was a room zero.</i>

1430
00:56:23,213 --> 00:56:29,385
THE FINAL GATE
THE BLACK ROOM

1431
00:56:30,762 --> 00:56:31,763
Let's go.

1432
00:56:33,515 --> 00:56:35,100
- Go first.
- Room 0.

1433
00:56:35,767 --> 00:56:37,017
Go.

1434
00:56:37,018 --> 00:56:39,312
KEEPING WATCH IN ALL DIRECTIONS

1435
00:56:41,731 --> 00:56:43,983
HEADING STRAIGHT WITH THE KEY CARD

1436
00:56:44,692 --> 00:56:46,401
There is something here.

1437
00:56:46,402 --> 00:56:48,363
- Is that a key?
- A key?

1438
00:56:50,490 --> 00:56:53,450
<i>We all realized
we had to place the key card on it.</i>

1439
00:56:53,451 --> 00:56:54,702
A LIGHT TAP

1440
00:56:55,662 --> 00:56:56,995
IT'S OPEN!

1441
00:56:56,996 --> 00:56:58,247
It worked.

1442
00:56:58,248 --> 00:56:59,082
What is it?

1443
00:57:01,459 --> 00:57:03,837
<i>We were finally in the last room.</i>

1444
00:57:04,337 --> 00:57:06,089
<i>We had reached the end.</i>

1445
00:57:11,136 --> 00:57:13,011
This must be the Black Room.

1446
00:57:13,012 --> 00:57:14,180
It's question zero.

1447
00:57:16,808 --> 00:57:18,767
- What do you think we need to do?
- Behold.

1448
00:57:18,768 --> 00:57:20,310
Behold!

1449
00:57:20,311 --> 00:57:22,147
- Behold is our go-to.
- We need a password.

1450
00:57:26,359 --> 00:57:29,445
It's something that has many keys
but opens no doors.

1451
00:57:29,446 --> 00:57:31,196
- Is this a trick question?
- I think so.

1452
00:57:31,197 --> 00:57:32,823
Is it a keyring?

1453
00:57:32,824 --> 00:57:34,116
A keyring?

1454
00:57:34,117 --> 00:57:36,201
Keyrings hold many keys.

1455
00:57:36,202 --> 00:57:37,995
But the ring itself…

1456
00:57:37,996 --> 00:57:41,623
A keyring holds many keys
but can't open doors on its own.

1457
00:57:41,624 --> 00:57:43,293
- Should we try it?
- Yes.

1458
00:57:43,877 --> 00:57:45,795
ENTERING KEYRING

1459
00:57:49,090 --> 00:57:50,382
- That's not it.
- It's wrong.

1460
00:57:50,383 --> 00:57:52,009
"I have many keys."

1461
00:57:52,010 --> 00:57:54,304
"I have many keys, yet open no doors."

1462
00:57:56,181 --> 00:57:57,222
I have an idea.

1463
00:57:57,223 --> 00:57:59,808
WHAT COULD IT BE?

1464
00:57:59,809 --> 00:58:01,394
It's a keyboard.

1465
00:58:01,978 --> 00:58:03,771
- It's a keyboard.
- A keyboard?

1466
00:58:04,898 --> 00:58:05,856
- Keyboard.
- This keyboard?

1467
00:58:05,857 --> 00:58:07,649
I mean a keyboard
like the one in front of us.

1468
00:58:07,650 --> 00:58:10,737
A keyboard has many keys
but can't open doors.

1469
00:58:12,322 --> 00:58:13,697
My gosh. I think you're right.

1470
00:58:13,698 --> 00:58:15,324
SURE OF THEIR ANSWER

1471
00:58:15,325 --> 00:58:16,867
TYPING "KEYBOARD" ON THE KEYBOARD

1472
00:58:16,868 --> 00:58:17,911
A, R, D.

1473
00:58:21,789 --> 00:58:23,040
Unbelievable.

1474
00:58:23,041 --> 00:58:24,917
ROOM 0 MISSION SUCCESSFUL

1475
00:58:24,918 --> 00:58:26,210
- That's crazy.
- I got goosebumps.

1476
00:58:26,211 --> 00:58:27,920
I could never have gotten that.

1477
00:58:27,921 --> 00:58:29,755
- Me neither.
- Same.

1478
00:58:29,756 --> 00:58:31,048
- It's all thanks to John.
- Right?

1479
00:58:31,049 --> 00:58:32,466
- I'd be stuck here forever.
- Right?

1480
00:58:32,467 --> 00:58:34,302
- I would have died here.
- Same.

1481
00:58:34,802 --> 00:58:35,928
Would you explode?

1482
00:58:35,929 --> 00:58:39,556
<i>You have successfully accessed
all data in the Black Room.</i>

1483
00:58:39,557 --> 00:58:40,474
THERE'S MORE?

1484
00:58:40,475 --> 00:58:43,311
<i>You have two choices.</i>

1485
00:58:44,062 --> 00:58:48,148
<i>You can export the data
or choose to delete it.</i>

1486
00:58:48,149 --> 00:58:49,816
TIME FOR A SUDDEN DECISION

1487
00:58:49,817 --> 00:58:51,401
If we export it…

1488
00:58:51,402 --> 00:58:53,445
- What do we do?
- This incredible technology…

1489
00:58:53,446 --> 00:58:55,572
- We can take it.
- It could be ours.

1490
00:58:55,573 --> 00:58:57,574
But we're supposed to delete it.

1491
00:58:57,575 --> 00:58:59,535
- That's true.
- That was our mission.

1492
00:58:59,536 --> 00:59:01,161
<i>In the case of an emergency,</i>

1493
00:59:01,162 --> 00:59:03,997
<i>you must enter the Black Room
to access the data</i>

1494
00:59:03,998 --> 00:59:05,707
<i>and delete all the files.</i>

1495
00:59:05,708 --> 00:59:07,334
We need to delete them.

1496
00:59:07,335 --> 00:59:10,295
But we went through so much today.

1497
00:59:10,296 --> 00:59:12,089
- I feel a little resentful.
- Me too.

1498
00:59:12,090 --> 00:59:13,590
You want to take it, right?

1499
00:59:13,591 --> 00:59:17,052
But if you think about it,
we can't do anything with it.

1500
00:59:17,053 --> 00:59:19,555
- There's not much we can do.
- Of course, there is.

1501
00:59:19,556 --> 00:59:21,848
- We can make a fortune.
- You need knowledge to use it.

1502
00:59:21,849 --> 00:59:25,769
<i>We weren't sure if we should
delete such explosive secrets.</i>

1503
00:59:25,770 --> 00:59:28,605
We did consider taking it.

1504
00:59:28,606 --> 00:59:30,649
But our assignment…

1505
00:59:30,650 --> 00:59:33,193
We were told to delete it.

1506
00:59:33,194 --> 00:59:35,571
We wanted to avoid trouble.

1507
00:59:35,572 --> 00:59:37,906
So, we agreed to delete it.

1508
00:59:37,907 --> 00:59:39,241
- Let's delete it.
- Okay.

1509
00:59:39,242 --> 00:59:40,450
I'll delete it.

1510
00:59:40,451 --> 00:59:41,703
We won't have time to use it.

1511
00:59:43,288 --> 00:59:47,040
<i>The Black Room data will now be deleted.</i>

1512
00:59:47,041 --> 00:59:48,667
I'm anxious that it's…

1513
00:59:48,668 --> 00:59:50,294
- Oh, it's going faster now.
- Let's be careful.

1514
00:59:50,295 --> 00:59:51,963
It's being deleted really fast.

1515
00:59:52,714 --> 00:59:55,966
<i>The Black Room data
has been completely deleted.</i>

1516
00:59:55,967 --> 00:59:57,050
Success!

1517
00:59:57,051 --> 00:59:59,553
<i>Now all the data has been deleted.</i>

1518
00:59:59,554 --> 01:00:01,138
- We did it.
<i>- According to protocol,</i>

1519
01:00:01,139 --> 01:00:03,682
<i>the Black Room will be destroyed.</i>

1520
01:00:03,683 --> 01:00:05,310
- What?
- What about us?

1521
01:00:06,686 --> 01:00:07,979
- We've been tricked.
- Come on.

1522
01:00:08,646 --> 01:00:10,105
- Come on.
- Hurry!

1523
01:00:10,106 --> 01:00:11,441
Hurry!

1524
01:00:12,650 --> 01:00:14,068
RUNNING FOR THEIR LIVES

1525
01:00:14,819 --> 01:00:16,612
The ceiling is coming down.

1526
01:00:16,613 --> 01:00:17,863
THE CEILING IS FALLING ALL OF A SUDDEN

1527
01:00:17,864 --> 01:00:18,780
Run!

1528
01:00:18,781 --> 01:00:22,327
<i>All users in the Black Room,
please evacuate.</i>

1529
01:00:28,374 --> 01:00:30,500
JOHN, YONG-JIN, AND HYE-RI
HAVE FALLEN BEHIND

1530
01:00:30,501 --> 01:00:31,753
- Keep running.
- Hurry.

1531
01:00:33,630 --> 01:00:34,589
Watch your head.

1532
01:00:38,134 --> 01:00:39,594
- What's happening?
- You didn't know?

1533
01:00:42,013 --> 01:00:43,014
It's all good.

1534
01:00:49,312 --> 01:00:51,438
- We're here.
- This is intense.

1535
01:00:51,439 --> 01:00:54,067
STILL IN SHOCK

1536
01:00:55,360 --> 01:00:57,070
We've completed the mission!

1537
01:01:00,448 --> 01:01:01,365
IT WAS HARD, BUT WE DID IT

1538
01:01:01,366 --> 01:01:02,449
Great job, everyone.

1539
01:01:02,450 --> 01:01:04,327
I feel like crying.

1540
01:01:05,536 --> 01:01:07,371
We did so much today.

1541
01:01:07,372 --> 01:01:09,831
- John, I never would've guessed keyboard.
- Seriously.

1542
01:01:09,832 --> 01:01:10,667
A SUDDEN BLACKOUT

1543
01:01:11,876 --> 01:01:13,210
- It was doable.
- Wait…

1544
01:01:13,211 --> 01:01:14,753
- The chokers…
- What?

1545
01:01:14,754 --> 01:01:17,089
THE CHOKERS HAVE TURNED RED

1546
01:01:17,090 --> 01:01:21,343
6 RED LIGHTS ROAMING IN SILENCE

1547
01:01:21,344 --> 01:01:23,011
THE LIGHT TURNS ON
AS IF NOTHING HAPPENED

1548
01:01:23,012 --> 01:01:24,055
I'm scared.

1549
01:01:26,516 --> 01:01:30,477
It feels like a lifetime
since we were first taken in this car.

1550
01:01:30,478 --> 01:01:32,270
<i>-Great job, agents.</i>
- It said, "Great job."

1551
01:01:32,271 --> 01:01:34,940
<i>You have successfully deleted</i>

1552
01:01:34,941 --> 01:01:39,653
<i>all the data in the Black Room
as top agents of XIN.</i>

1553
01:01:39,654 --> 01:01:41,071
OVERWHELMED

1554
01:01:41,072 --> 01:01:42,781
<i>- Hello.</i>
- Hello.

1555
01:01:42,782 --> 01:01:46,034
<i>-We are NIX.</i>
- What?

1556
01:01:46,035 --> 01:01:48,495
<i>We are NIX.</i>

1557
01:01:48,496 --> 01:01:50,789
<i>We have taken down XIN,</i>

1558
01:01:50,790 --> 01:01:55,253
<i>and thanks to your efforts,
we have been able to acquire</i>

1559
01:01:55,837 --> 01:01:59,297
<i>all the important data needed
to recreate the world order.</i>

1560
01:01:59,298 --> 01:02:00,465
What?

1561
01:02:00,466 --> 01:02:03,761
<i>As a reward, we will spare your lives.</i>

1562
01:02:05,096 --> 01:02:07,597
<i>At least for today.</i>

1563
01:02:07,598 --> 01:02:08,598
- What?
- Oh, my gosh.

1564
01:02:08,599 --> 01:02:10,059
<i>Have a safe journey home.</i>

1565
01:02:14,147 --> 01:02:15,898
- What?
- We were tricked.

1566
01:02:25,783 --> 01:02:27,534
This is so annoying.
Let's throw a smoke grenade.

1567
01:02:27,535 --> 01:02:29,661
- Here?
- Yes, let's throw one.

1568
01:02:29,662 --> 01:02:30,954
It's been a really tough day.

1569
01:02:30,955 --> 01:02:32,248
I have a canker sore.

1570
01:02:34,333 --> 01:02:36,376
It's been a profound experience.

1571
01:02:36,377 --> 01:02:37,753
You're not crying, are you?

1572
01:02:37,754 --> 01:02:39,338
That was quite
a welcoming party for Gabee.

1573
01:02:40,423 --> 01:02:42,132
- Great job today.
- You worked so hard.

1574
01:02:42,133 --> 01:02:44,176
- You went through a lot.
- You did great.

1575
01:02:44,177 --> 01:02:46,344
- It's different from what you see, right?
- Isn't it different?

1576
01:02:46,345 --> 01:02:48,889
- I didn't think it would be this hard.
- You did amazing.

1577
01:02:48,890 --> 01:02:50,724
Is this the real world?

1578
01:02:50,725 --> 01:02:51,808
Where are we?

1579
01:02:51,809 --> 01:02:53,018
It's so nice to get fresh air.

1580
01:02:53,019 --> 01:02:56,271
Does this mean
we should have exported the file?

1581
01:02:56,272 --> 01:02:58,231
Yes, who said we should delete it?

1582
01:02:58,232 --> 01:02:59,274
Whose idea was it?

1583
01:02:59,275 --> 01:03:00,358
I said I was resentful.

1584
01:03:00,359 --> 01:03:01,943
Me too.

1585
01:03:01,944 --> 01:03:04,571
- It did bring us closer together.
- It did.

1586
01:03:04,572 --> 01:03:05,823
All right, then.

1587
01:03:09,494 --> 01:03:11,119
- It's going to stick in my head.
- Yes.

1588
01:03:11,120 --> 01:03:15,999
- I really think it has brought us closer.
- Yes, I feel closer to you all.

1589
01:03:16,000 --> 01:03:17,459
It was only your first day.

1590
01:03:17,460 --> 01:03:18,877
- We did great.
- You did amazing.

1591
01:03:18,878 --> 01:03:20,170
Should we do it one last time?

1592
01:03:20,171 --> 01:03:21,005
Ready?

1593
01:03:24,967 --> 01:03:25,926
Let's go again!

1594
01:03:25,927 --> 01:03:28,304
Gabee, you got one wrong.

1595
01:03:29,305 --> 01:03:32,557
- After all that, you got one step wrong!
- Stop that.

1596
01:03:32,558 --> 01:03:34,267
I did not!

1597
01:03:34,268 --> 01:03:35,393
Go, LACHICA!

1598
01:03:35,394 --> 01:03:37,313
Oh, come on!

1599
01:03:46,072 --> 01:03:51,077
Subtitle translation by: Hannah Og Nam
